title: black bottoms
directions: In a small bowl, mix the cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and pinch of salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: shipwreck
directions: Butter a deep casserole dish or an oblong pan.
Make a layer of sliced potatoes.
Top with a layer of sliced onions.
Crumble the hamburger over the onions.
Top with the carrots, celery and rice.
(Note:
Salt and paprika each layer lightly.)

title: italian casserole
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, in a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook ground beef and onions until onions are tender (about 10 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt, basil, oregano leaves, sugar and pepper; cook 2 more minutes to blend flavors.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, evenly spoon 1/3 of meat mixture; arrange one-half of potatoes on top.
Repeat layering, ending with meat mixture.
Cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for one hour or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Remove foil; sprinkle evenly with Mozzarella cheese; bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes for easier cutting. Makes 8 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix chopped onion and ground beef.
Fry until brown.
Drain juice when done.
Add all beans.
Add A-1, ketchup, garlic powder, liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce to suit taste.
Add brown sugar to suit taste.
Mix well.
Pour mix into 9 x 13 casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Lay bacon slices on top. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, Wesson oil, sugar and apricot juice.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Empty cake onto plate.

title: mini lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
In large baking dish, layer noodles and sauce. Mix egg, parsley and Ricotta cheese in bowl; spread mixture over 1st layer.
Spread over 1/2 cup of Mozzarella.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add oats to mixture.

title: `salsa' chile jalapeno in tomato juice
directions: In a big pot, put first 5 ingredients, cook for 1/2 hr.
Turn off heat; add 1 qt. tomato juice and blend/mash in blender.
Pour back into pot, add the rest ingredients except jalapeos.
Cook for 10 min.
(If cooked too long the jalapeos get too soft.) Spoon into hot jars, put lids on and let cool to seal.
Finished! These are very good.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix white cake mix, strawberry jello and flour.
Add water, eggs, oil and strawberries.
Pour batter in 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Boil for 6 to 8 minutes; remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter and oats. Stir and spoon out onto wax paper or tinfoil.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: carrots elegante
directions: Cook carrots, covered in 1/2 inch of boiling water 8 minutes. Drain.
Place carrots in 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in raisins, butter, honey, lemon juice and ginger.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix together and knead 6 to 8 minutes.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in the sugar, vinegar and vanilla.
Continue beating until very stiff.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until firm.

title: suez mezze (middle east chicken balls)
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Put
chicken and bread through fine blade of food grinder twice or process with metal blade in food processor until
ground.
Place
ground
chicken mixture in medium bowl; mix in egg yolk, parsley, onion, salt, pepper, cumin, garlic powder and
turmeric.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Shape mixture	into
balls
using 1 rounded teaspoonful of the chicken mixture	for
each;
roll each ball lightly in flour to coat.
Pour oil
in
2-quart saucepan to a level of 1 inch.
Heat oil to
Fry
appetizers
at a time
in oil until golden, 3 to
4	minutes.
Drain
on
paper towel.
Keep warm in 200° oven,
if
desired,
until
ready to serve.
Makes about 20.

title: shredded squash relish
directions: Mix squash and onion with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain. Mix remaining ingredients.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients, except pimento.
Bring to a boil.
Mix squash and onions and bring to second boil.
Add pimento.
Place in jars and seal.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour in two 8-inch pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: mama's chicken-broccoli pastries
directions: Filling can be prepared up to 24 hours in advance and cook broccoli in microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, then remove and drain.
Place butter in bowl and heat on High to melt butter (450°).
Stir in flour, dill weed, salt, mustard, garlic powder and pepper.
Blend in milk and microwave on High for 4 minutes or until thick.
Stir 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Place cream cheese in separate bowl; microwave until soft (30 seconds).
Add to sauce and beat.
Add chicken and broccoli; mix.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll out crescent rolls and press into 4 (6-inch) squares.
Spoon in mixture on 1/2 square.
Fold over.
Pinch edges.
Place on ungreased sheet; brush with egg and dill weed.
Bake 18 to 24 minutes until golden brown.

title: polar bear cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and white chocolate stars over very low heat.
Add remaining ingredients; drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: cracker barrel hash browns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray pan (12 x 12 x 4-inch or 9 x 13-inch) with Pam.
In large bowl, combine soup, margarine, salt, pepper, onion and cheese.
Gently mix in potatoes and pour into prepared dish or pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
If not brown enough, place under broiler.

title: walnutty caramels
directions: Line pan with foil. Lightly butter foil.

title: pizza noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles, uncovered, until done.
Drain.
While noodles cook, combine ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet. Cook, uncovered, until done.
Stir tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms and seasoning into meat mixture after draining.
Mix well.
Add cooked noodles.

title: banana split torte
directions: Melt one stick margarine; mix with crumbs and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream 2 sticks margarine with powdered sugar. Add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over crumbs.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Slice bananas; sprinkle with lemon juice. Arrange bananas over creamed mixture.
Mix 1/2 of Cool Whip with drained pineapple.
Spread over bananas.
Cover with remainder of Cool Whip.
Garnish with maraschino cherries and chopped nuts.

title: grilling sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients and stir over low flame until well mixed.
Baste meat on grill.

title: apple or cherry bread
directions: Pour all ingredients into bowl; mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cheese squares
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine and press in 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. "Cool." Reserve 1/4 cup and set aside.

title: sausage-egg delight
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13 pan. Beat eggs. Add milk and rest of ingredients. Cover. LET STAND OVERNIGHT. Bake for 1 hour at 325° with foil over pan. Uncover and cook another 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: poor man's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating about 1 minute each.
Flavoring and salt can be added now.
Add 1 cup flour, then 1/2 cup milk, then 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup milk, ending with 1 cup flour, beating well after each addition.
Bake in 1 large tube pan at 300° for 2 hours or 2 loaf pans 1 hour and 50 minutes at 300° (grease and flour pans).
If you do not like mixed flavor as listed use 3 teaspoons lemon or 2 teaspoons lemon and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add other ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until thick, stirring constantly; pour into serving dish.
Let

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Put yolks in a bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix until well blended.
Spoon back into eggs.

title: harvest beets
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and vinegar in this order in a saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over prepared beets in a saucepan and let stand on back of stove for 30 minutes.
Put on low heat just before serving.
Add butter.

title: easy potatoes
directions: You will also need Pam and foil.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and jalapeno pepper.
Add tomatoes. Cook for about 10 minutes.
Add the American cheese until melted. Stir together while cooking.
Place 1 large tortilla shell on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer with hamburger mixture.
Continue with another tortilla shell and hamburger mixture.
Spread Cheddar cheese on top layer.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet. Add onion and cook slightly. Add broccoli and soup. Stir well and simmer for 5 minutes. Add Cheez Whiz and rice. Simmer 5 more minutes.
Pour in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemonade
directions: Cook juice and	sugar
together over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar
is	melted	and juice is syrupy.
Pour into a clean jar and store in the refrigerator.

title: cherry chiffon salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into serving bowl. Chill.
Makes 12 to 14 servings. Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Chill time: 30 minutes.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Mix all together well.
Freeze in oblong pan or in muffin liners.
May also use whole cranberry sauce or blueberry pie filling.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Saute onions, celery and bell peppers.
Add flour, chicken broth and milk.
Add soup, pimentos and 1/2 cup butter.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add chicken and spaghetti.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; return to oven for 5 more minutes.

title: zesty meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in hot oil until lightly browned; drain. Place meatballs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: cheese cake(light-no-bake)
directions: Mix together and press into a 9-inch pie shell pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool before filling with cheese filling.

title: chocolate dip
directions: Melt chocolate and butter. Add sugar, cornstarch and vanilla. Stir well together. Add water. Cook until slightly thickened. Pour over cake and serve.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash, peel and dice potatoes; boil potatoes until done (not mushy).
Drain and place in lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt 6 tablespoons of butter in medium saucepan; blend flour, then gradually add cream.
Stir constantly; heat to a boil. Add salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter; stir into bread crumbs.
Mix until coated; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In the pot noodles were cooked in mix hot noodles and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients to noodles and mix well.
Add cinnamon, teaspoon or more, and mix well.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
If kugel looks too wet, remove cover and bake a little longer.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve hot.
We use as a side dish with baked ham, roasted chicken or turkey.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Add zucchini, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix well, then gradually blend in flour.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: low-fat muffin surprises
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat together egg, milk and cooking oil; add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin tin cups 1/3 full.
Place a teaspoon jelly or jam atop batter in muffin tin.
Fill muffin tin cups with remaining batter.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: congealed cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in 1 cup hot water.
Let thicken.
Mix pineapple with cream cheese and add all other ingredients.

title: cookie cutter cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add creamed butter.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out.
Bake at 275° for 40 minutes.

title: canned tomatoes
directions: Wash, peel and core tomatoes.
Pack in jars with 1 teaspoon salt to a quart jar.
Put on a tray and place in oven.
Cook at 200° for 1 hour.
Heat tops before you fill.
Close jars.
Put in oven, jar, top and all.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring water, tea and cloves to a boil; simmer for 5 minutes. Strain. Then add sugar, orange juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice. Mix well.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Spread Tater Tots and then broccoli in dish.
Melt margarine in frying pan.
Saute sliced onions, including tops in butter.
Mix soup, 2/3 of cheese and sour cream with onions.
Pour over potatoes and broccoli.
If too thick, I add about 3/4 cup milk and a little more sour cream to make it soupy; it cooks down thick.
Add remaining cheese to top.
(Add more cheese if you like.)
I add Mozzarella cheese to top.
It's great!!

title: glorified rice
directions: Rice should be cooked, but not mushy.
Mix all the ingredients, except whipping cream.
Allow to stand 1 hour.
Fold in whipped cream just before serving.
Garnish with cherries, strawberries or sliced peaches.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bones.
Mix celery and chicken soup in saucepan, plus chicken broth and heat over low heat.
Pour over Pepperidge dressing.
Melt margarine and pour over dressing. Mix well, may use hands.
Place half in well-greased baking dish. Place chicken, after tearing into small pieces, over mixture.
Add finely chopped eggs to chicken.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Add remaining dressing mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown beef and chopped onion until done.
Place beef and onion in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Slice peeled potatoes over top of beef onion mixture.
Pour corn over top of potatoes.
Top with buttered crumbs if desired.
Bake at 350° covered for 1 hour.

title: upside-down vegetable cake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening. Combine egg and milk; add to dry ingredients, stirring until mixed. Arrange hot seasoned vegetables in bottom of greased shallow baking dish.
Add vegetable stock, dot with butter, cover with first mixture and bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn out on a serving plate with vegetables on top.
Serve with tomato or mushroom sauce.
Serves 6.

title: nonfat potatoes
directions: Slice the potatoes and sprinkle with parsley flakes, Molly McButter and garlic salt.
Add water.
Cook in covered microwave dish until done.
Stir occasionally and check with toothpick for doneness.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger with taco seasoning; drain.
Do not mix until ready to serve!!

title: drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pan.
Put all ingredients in bowl.
Dump a spoonful of batter into a smaller bowl that has flour in it.
Shape the biscuits and put it in the greased pan. Pat the top with knuckles.
Do the rest of the biscuits.
Put in oven and cook until done or as brown as you like them.
In a gas oven, approximately 15 minutes.
In an electric oven, approximately 20 minutes.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: *The berries can be mashed or a few quartered and the balance blender pureed.

title: party salad topping
directions: Mix well and refrigerate until serving time.

title: chicken enchiladas a la rhodes
directions: In a
pot
of water, place 1 whole chicken, making sure you have enough
water to cover.
Add 1 whole onion.
Add some salt and
pepper.
Simmer
until chicken is done.
Meat should start to fall
from
the
bones.
Place
chicken
in a bowl to cool. Debone chicken
and put meat in a pan.
Cover with some red chili sauce and simmer for 10 minutes;
let cool.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flavoring.
With spoon add flour and oats until well mixed.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Press with fork on lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
When cool, put in cookie tin and refrigerate. Will keep a month and get better every day.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer in order in large bowl.
Let stand in the layered form for 24 hours in refrigerator or until ready to serve.
Mix right before serving. You can add a little salt if needed.
You can make 1/2 this recipe.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add molasses and egg.
Mix dry ingredients together and sift.
Form into balls; press down and pat with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: 24-hour pea salad
directions: Mix all together in shallow pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Use large frying pan to fry bacon.
Add onion; cook until onion is golden.
Add egg; stirring as it cooks.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and hard-boiled eggs.
Add cooked potatoes. Serve hot.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage after removing green leaves.
Do not shred stalk.
Shred carrot.
Mix all remaining ingredients together to make sauce and add to shredded cabbage and carrot.
Toss together. Cover and let sit in refrigerator a couple of hours.

title: hamburger rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 4 cups flour and yeast. Combine warm water, oil, sugar and salt.
Add to dry ingredients in bowl.
Add eggs.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: quiche
directions: Combine eggs, milk, pepper and baking powder.
Beat well. Stir in ham and cheese.
Add onion.
Spoon into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until firm in center.

title: magic peach cobbler
directions: In cold oven, place stick of butter in large cobbler bowl. Turn oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together in a bowl. When butter is melted, take bowl out of oven and pour mixture into the hot butter, then put peaches on top.
Bake for 1 hour and take out of oven.

title: cleaning mixture
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in well marked bottle.
Good for cleaning walls, woodwork, all surfaces.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350° (325° glass).

title: ground beef surprise
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add salt, sugar, pepper and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes. Cream together the cream cheese, Ricotta cheese and onion salt. Stir well until smooth and softened.
Using a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, layer noodles, meat mixture and cream mixture.
Repeat until all gone. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix well by hand and make small balls.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours or over night.
Melt block of chocolate and dip balls until coated.
Put on wax paper to dry.
Put in tight container, this will freeze well.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix and put on a pizza pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine in aluminum pie pan or similar metal pan over heat.
Add 3/4 cup brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped pecans.
Mix these well.
Remove from heat.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients until light.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carolina cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Add onion and pepper; toss together in a large bowl.
Mix the sugar, salt, mustard and celery seed in a small saucepan.
Add vinegar and oil; let come to a boil over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cabbage; toss well.
Allow to cool to room temperature in a nonporous container, then cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: martha's chili
directions: In a large skillet, slowly brown the garlic and onions in olive oil; stir and cook until tender.
Raise heat, add meat and cook until done.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook about 45 minutes more.

title: mustard substitute
directions: Blend water, flour and turmeric.
Pour into saucepan and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Return to blender and add garlic and lemon juice.
Mix well and chill.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix sausage with biscuit mix until crumbly. Add cheese and a little milk to hold. Roll in small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° until brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix together sauce ingredients.
Spread chicken pieces in baking pan.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until batter is smooth and well blended.
Pour into a greased tube pan with removable bottom. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Remove from oven and glaze white hot.

title: saopaw stew
directions: Brown steak in butter.
Add onion, garlic, and mushrooms; cook until onion is sort of soft.
Add the squash and tomatoes; cook until squash is almost done.
Add the mushroom soup.
Simmer until squash is done.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix and bake ingredients at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir in 1/2 hour.

title: rich pound cake
directions: Preheat oven.
Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemony (about 5 minutes).
Add to butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form when beater is slowly raised. Add flour gradually to butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add egg whites and mix gently.
Turn batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake for 65 to 70 minutes at 350° or until center tests clean.
Cool for about 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 3-inch oblong pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch squares.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chili day cornbread
directions: Add corn and sliced hot dogs to cornbread mix.
Spoon chili over, spread shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: portuguese hot dog appetizers
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1-inch pieces.
Place all ingredients in electric
skillet.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes, until mixture thickens.
Serve hot, right out of the skillet.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In a large clear bowl, fill it halfway with torn lettuce. Layer the rest of the ingredients on top of the lettuce in the order listed.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve.

title: barbecue turkey sandwiches(this is a favorite because it's quick, easy and tasty!)
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter.
Stir in sauces and spices.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in turkey pieces.
Serve on buns.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Save drippings.
Saute onions and celery in drippings.
Layer rice, sausage, onions and celery. Spread mushroom soup, then chicken noodle soup.
Pour 1 1/2 cans of water over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat egg; add sugar and beat well.
Add Wesson oil and beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt and beat well.
Add apples and nuts; mix well with hands.
Cook in greased, floured pan for 40 minutes (or until done) in 325° oven.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, combine potatoes, onion and salt.
Add enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook until tender and drain.
Place in lightly greased casserole dish.
In a saucepan, combine margarine, flour, milk and cheese.
Heat over low heat, stirring frequently, until thick.
Pour over potato mixture and bake for 45 minutes.

title: jalapeno-potato soup
directions: Ham meat doesn't fry much, so put grease in with it when you fry it.
Take the meat out and pour the grease in a bowl.
Sprinkle sugar on the hot frying pan.
Pour about 1/2 cup of water on the skillet.
It'll fry like lightning, so just cook it until it's hot, about 1 minute.
Pour it over the grease in the bowl and when you get your red.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken about 15 to 20 minutes. Set aside. Line the bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with tortillas. Layer cooked chicken on bottom. Add in layers bell pepper and onion. Mix together tomatoes, mushroom soup and chicken soup. Pour mixture on the layers. Top with shredded cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Put cheese on and bake until cheese melts.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook pinto beans, onion, bell pepper and tomatoes.
When done, add sugar, Tabasco, salt, pepper and paste.

title: jackie's chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain enough noodles to fill your casserole dish. While noodles are cooking, mix mayonnaise, chicken, salt and pepper in casserole dish.
Warm chicken soup, milk and cheese in saucepan. Combine noodles and chicken mixture.
Pour soup mixture over noodles and stir until well mixed.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 425° or until bubbly.

title: "down home" barbeque sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix.
Combine remaining 4 ingredients and add to dry mixture, stirring well.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend honey and milk together; add flour gradually, stirring until smooth.
Add eggs, corn, butter and salt.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with allspice.
Place baking dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until custard is set.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: rotel
directions: Bring all
ingredients	to a hard boil.
Lower heat and let simmer for	1 hour.
Pour into pint jars. Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and
teaspoon	sugar
to each jar. Seal.
Process in boiling water bath for a few minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs, then add oil, oleo, sugar and zucchini.
Sift and measure out 3 cups flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add sifted ingredients to cream mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy hollandaise sauce
directions: Into an electric blender, put the egg yolks, lemon juice and salt.
Heat the butter to bubbling, but do not brown.
Turn motor on low speed and add hot butter gradually.
Then blend about 15 seconds more, or until sauce is thickened and smooth.

title: strawberry bruschetta
directions: Slice bread into 1/2-inch slices; arrange on a cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven about 10 minutes or until golden brown. Turn oven setting to broil.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to oil mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
This will be extremely thick.
Put into greased tube pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mock angel food cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together 2 times and add boiling milk.
Add beaten egg whites.
Bake 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: plaza park squares
directions: Mix by hand and press in greased 9 x 11 pan.

title: coconut pecan ice cream topping
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sweetened condensed milk, egg yolks and margarine.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thick and bubbly, about 8 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Makes 2 cups.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls out on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° when brown as you like.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mix.
Spread on crust and top with chopped raw vegetables.

title: easy crust peach pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Combine butter, sugar, flour and milk in mixing bowl and mix well.
Pour half of dough mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine peaches, juice and all, salt and spices.
Mix well. Pour over mixture in casserole, then add remaining dough on top. Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then turn oven to 400° and bake for another 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a hard boil. Combine other ingredients.
Pour hot vinegar and sugar over the mixture and let stand overnight in a covered container in refrigerator.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Combine sugar, water and salt in medium saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add 2 cups raw unskinned peanuts and continue to cook until the syrup crystallizes.
Pour into a large flat pan and spread out.
Cook at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie(diabetic)
directions: Beat egg substitute and add, in order, spices, salt, sweeteners, margarine, pumpkin and milk.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until it tests done.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over melted margarine. Top evenly with coconut, then milk.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Spread chocolate chips evenly over hot coconut layer.
Cool 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: 'possum on board
directions: Attach possum firmly to board.
Boil in tub of salted water for 1 hour and 26 minutes and 14 seconds.
Remove possum and board; pop into preheated 416° oven for 2 hours and 59 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Discard possum.
Eat board.

title: cool summer dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Blend thoroughly. Chill several hours before serving. Makes 3 cups.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix margarine, cake mix
and 1 egg; add nuts and put in 9 x 13-inch greased
pan.
Mix	cream
cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar. Beat
good;	pour
over nut mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chews
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk. Stir in nuts and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Form in balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mandel bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together for 4 minutes.
Add oil and beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Add flour, salt and baking powder (mixed together).
Mix by hand.
Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly by hand.
Mix will be sticky.
Using two ungreased cookie sheets or jelly roll pans, make 4 long rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Cut in pan and turn on sides. Return to oven to brown sides.

title: orange honey cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Mix eggs, sugar, honey and vegetable oil with an electric mixer until blended. Dissolve coffee in 1/2 cup warm water. Mix into batter with orange juice. Mix in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice and salt. Mix for 1 minute or until smooth. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake 65 to 75 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove to rack. Cool 10 minutes. Invert and cool completely. Makes 12 servings.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add onion rings last.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour 1 cup of boiling water over 1/2 cup of corn meal; stir. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 1-quart baking dish and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown. Serve with a spoon; top with butter.

title: melt in your mouth blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Cream shortening and salt and vanilla.
Add remaining sugar and egg yolks and beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients, then milk.
Fold in egg whites then add berries.
Take a bit of the flour and roll berries in it so they won't settle.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: frosties(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Melt chocolate chips over warm water.
Remove and add corn syrup and orange juice.
Mix sugar, crumbs and nuts in large bowl. Pour liquid over all and mix well with spoon and then use hands for final mixing.
Grease hands with butter and then roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in powdered sugar.
These are best if served 24 hours or later or can be frozen as they keep very well.
Defrost and they are ready to serve.

title: best baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking pan. Top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bacon browns.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Hand mix the butter, sugar and peanut butter together.
Add graham cracker crumbs and mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt the chocolate chips in a pan and spread over the other stuff.
Cut while chocolate covering is still warm.

title: bailey's
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: corn souffle
directions: Cook frozen corn with a small amount of water, salt and butter.
Stir flour into milk and add to corn.
Add sugar, egg yolks and pepper.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold corn mixture into egg whites.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: special k cookies
directions: Use ungreased pans.
Cream together in the usual way.
Put on pans by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: see's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Melt chocolate chips and butter together.
Add sugar mixture to chocolate mixture.
Pour into buttered dish and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Never fails.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add
sugar
and
cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs,
one
at
a
time,
beating well. Sift baking powder and salt with flour.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavorings and
nuts last.
Bake 2 hours at 300° in a greased and floured
tube
pan.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: eggplant stew(berenjenas guisadas)
directions: Cut ham and vegetables in small pieces and fry lightly.
Add water and eggplant.
Add salt to taste; stir.
Cook at low heat for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Line pan with whole graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 pudding over them; top with another layer of graham crackers and cover with rest of pudding. Refrigerate.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Mix seasoning, cream cheese and cottage cheese in a mixing bowl.
Spread mixture onto a 10-inch platter.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes, sliced black olives and shredded lettuce. Serve with plain tortilla chips.

title: holbrook rolls
directions: Use electric mixer. Mix warm water, yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar. Let ferment.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Drain asparagus, reserve juice and add water to make 2 cups. Combine juice mixture, sugar, vinegar and salt and bring to a boil.
Soften gelatin in cold water and add to hot mixture.
Stir until blended.
Chill until egg white consistency.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill until firm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil and mash squash.
Saute chopped onion in butter.
Mix well with squash.
Beat eggs and mix with squash. Season and bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour the mushroom soup over squash.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake again for 20 minutes.

title: mamma's berry cobbler
directions: Place berries in ovenproof pan or casserole dish.
Add vanilla. Bake until crust is brown.
Remove from oven. Cut crust into pan of berries.
Place the other crust on berries and bake until brown.
Remove from oven.

title: nathan and patty's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oleo and sugar until very fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each addition.
Fold in flour and vanilla.
Add 3 to 4 cups chopped pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Slice cake in three layers.
Cream sugar and cream cheese. Mix well and add powdered sugar.
Mix well and add Cool Whip. Spread on each layer and top each layer with pie filling.
Spread on sides and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix together all ingredients.
Top with cheese cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Serve with the wide Frito chips and a margarita!

title: oyster crackers snacks
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Put crackers in large bowl; set aside. Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly in a small bowl. Pour and mix with crackers. Be sure all crackers are coated with mixture. Put into a 9 x 2 x 13 baking pan and put in oven for 15 minutes. Stir again thoroughly halfway through baking time.

title: kool-aid lemon pies
directions: Stir in Cool Whip last. Stir well.
Pour into pie crust.
I crumble vanilla wafers on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together and refrigerate 4 hours.
Shape into a ball and roll in finely chopped parsley or nuts.
Chill until used.
Serve with crackers.

title: light and creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, pie filling and pumpkin pie spice in a mixing bowl. Beat at lowest speed. Mix until well blended, about 1 minute. Fold in 2 1/2 cups of whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours. Top with remaining whipped topping.

title: pierre's delicacy
directions: Put ice cream in your favorite serving dish.
Pour liquor over top.
Place cherry on top and serve.

title: clean your plate casserole
directions: Cook the noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef and onion; add next 7 ingredients. In a small bowl, mix together until smooth the sour cream and cream cheese.
Combine the 2 mixtures together and mix well.

title: frost bite
directions: In a Hurricane glass, from the Laniki machine, parfait strawberry Margarita and Madori Margarita.
Garnish with a fresh strawberry.

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix juices and sugar in a pot.
Tie all spices in cheesecloth. Put in liquid and bring to a boil.
When at a full boil, take out bag of spices and drop in sticks of cinnamon.

title: chewy fudge brownies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in chocolate, vanilla and flour.
Add nuts.
Bake in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer the following ingredients in a flat dish.
Bottom layer: bean dip.
Next layer:
avocado dip that has been thawed.
Next, spread picante sauce.
Next layer:
sour cream.
The top layer is a mixture of tomatoes and green onions, chopped up in small pieces.

title: garbage(aka nacho supreme salad)
directions: Cook meat according to taco mix directions.
To serve, layer corn chips, meat, Cheez Whiz, sour cream, lettuce, tomato and sauce or salsa.
Enjoy!

title: baked fish and dressing
directions: Place perch in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt butter and saute onions until slightly yellow.
Add stuffing and blend well.
Spread dressing mix over fish.
Cover with foil and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil for 10 minutes to brown dressing.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Note:
You can add crushed pineapple and nuts as well.

title: fudge
directions: Blend sugar, cream of tartar and cocoa.
Add milk; mix well. Place on low heat.
Stir until reaches boiling point.
Then do not stir.
Boil until soft ball stage in cup of cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter or oleo and vanilla.
Place pan in cold water.
Let set until cool to fingertips.
Then beat; put nuts in and put on wax paper.
Drop by spoon or you may cut it.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange cut apples in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add water. Combine topping ingredients; cut in butter until mixture is coated but still in crumbs.
Place on top of apples.
Cover pan with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover pan and bake 30 minutes more at 350°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients using half the almonds.
Pour into small baking dish and sprinkle with remaining almonds.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot with Triscuits.

title: mark's meatball and gravy recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into medium meatballs.
Deep fry in oil until golden brown.
Make homemade gravy or use package gravy or jar gravy.
Completely cover meatballs.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Simmer several hours over low heat.
Stir often.

title: sausage and noodles
directions: Brown onion and sausage in large skillet.
Drain.
Add soup and water; mix well.
Add noodles; turn heat to medium.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli per package instructions.
Drain and press out moisture.
Combine soup, Miracle Whip and 2 well beaten eggs and onion, chopped. Blend in broccoli.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Melt margarine and add to stuffing crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Mash squash and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish and top with bread crumbs and 3/4 cup grated cheese.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift 2 cups flour with salt and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Dice orange slices; mix with 1/2 cup flour.
Add candy mixture to first mixture.
Stir in coconut, chopped nuts and oats.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Press with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mom's cinnamon rolls
directions: Make White Bread recipe as instructed, except add the sugar and cinnamon to the milk mixture.
After allowing dough to raise the first time, roll dough flat on a floured surface.
Spread melted butter, then sugar and cinnamon to individual preference. May add 1/2 cup Karo syrup, nuts and raisins, if desired.
Roll into large roll; cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place flat on greased cookie sheet.
Cover with light cloth; allow to raise for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
May be frosted, if desired.

title: nutty caramel corn
directions: *One cup unpopped corn is 6 quarts freshly popped.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in a grocery bag.
Combine sugar, syrup and butter in a bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and microwave 3 minutes more.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn in a bag.
Stir with a large wooden spoon.
Fold over top of bag and shake.
Microwave 1 minute; shake.
Repeat.
Repeat again. Spread on a waxed paper to dry.

title: orange salad
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Dissolve jello completely.
Cool slightly.
Fold in 1 pint orange sherbet.
Add mandarin oranges, drained.
Refrigerate until firm.
Can be used in mold.

title: soda pop salad
directions: Stir jello in water.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Chop cream cheese until fine.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread #2
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Add eggs, bananas and butter to mixture.

title: my coconut pie
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and flour together. Add eggs, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for approximately 50 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: upper crust carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients and sift into large bowl.
Add
remaining
ingredients
and
mix
well. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Place
wax paper in bottom of pan. Pour batter into pan.
Bake
minutes or until top springs back to touch.
Let cake
cool
on
rack in pan before removing.

title: crab muffins
directions: Mix; spread on muffins.
Bake in oven for 5 to 8 minutes until tops start to brown.

title: eggplant-zucchini casserole(low-fat)
directions: Combine tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, black pepper, spices and garlic.
Mix well.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, arrange 1/2 of eggplant slices in a single layer.
Top with 1/2 of zucchini slices, celery, spaghetti, onion and green pepper.
Then spread 1/2 of cheese on top, then spoon 1/2 of tomato mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake covered at 350° for about an hour or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 8.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Mix with orange sections, orange juice and pineapple.
Mix instant pudding according to directions on box and put on top of chilled jello mixture.

title: easy buffalo chicken wings
directions: Melt butter in microwave-safe bowl or small saucepan.
Stir in hot sauce.
Arrange wing sections on baking sheet.
Pour butter/ hot sauce mixture over all and stir to coat sections evenly with sauce.
Bake at 375° about 15 to 20 minutes to desired crispness, turning about halfway through cooking time.
Serve with celery sticks and Ranch or Blue cheese dressing, if desired.
Yields about 16 to 20 pieces.

title: blue cheese eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Combine in saucepan with chopped onion.
Cook 7 to 10 minutes or until eggplant is tender when pierced with a fork.
Drain immediately.

title: inside-out ravioli
directions: Brown the meat and onion in oil well.
Cook spinach and reserve liquid; add water to liquid to make one cup.
Add to meat the spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Cook noodles.
Add cheese, bread crumbs, beaten eggs and butter.
Fold into spinach and water.
Put in layers in a 9 1/2 x 12-inch pan.
Start with meat sauce and end with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: ham and cheese crescent roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent roll dough into 8 rectangles, sealing perforations.
Place 1 slice ham on each rectangle.
Spread with cream cheese.
Roll up, pinching seams. Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Cut each roll into 6 portions.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake 12 to 17 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Mix juice, sugar, cornstarch and eggs. Slowly bring to boil and cook until thickens. While still hot, pour over the tidbits and marshmallows. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry dessert(frozen)
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients in a large casserole dish. Save 1/2 cup of this mixture to sprinkle over the top later.
Set aside.
Put the rest in the oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Stir often and smooth out to form a crust on the bottom of dish.
Mix egg whites, lemon juice, sugar and strawberries.
Beat until fluffy.
Set aside while you beat the whipping cream.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar, one tablespoon at a time and a pinch of salt. Combine fluffy mix and whipping cream mix.
Pour over crust, then sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup you saved from the bottom of the casserole.
Freeze.
This is cut into squares to serve.
It is best to let it sit about 10 minutes before serving.

title: squash dressing
directions: Chop onions and cook in butter or margarine until onions look clear.
Mash squash.
Combine onion, butter and slightly beaten eggs.
Add soup and bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix and pour in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet bread cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Prepare 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan with shortening and flour.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Makes a lot.
Halves well.

title: new-fashioned fettuccine alfredo
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat; stir in 3/4 cup light cream.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add fettuccine to skillet.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup cream, cheese, pepper, nutmeg and salt; cook 1 minute.
If desired, serve with additional cheese and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together the broccoli, onion, eggs, cheese, salt and margarine.
Add cornbread mix and flour.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mrs. holley's real fudge icing
directions: Mix everything but vanilla.
(I use a large Teflon skillet.) Place over slow heat and boil. Start timing when there's a rolling boil.
Cook exactly 1 minute. Add vanilla. Cool, then beat. Add pecans, if desired.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar before adding the eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix it thoroughly, then fold in the blueberries.
Bake the batter in greased muffin tins at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: maggie's hush puppies
directions: NOTE:
These amounts are guesstimates, but should work well.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes and serve over Fritos chips.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.

title: mother's zucchini bread
directions: Mix until smooth, then pour in small loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baker's dough
directions: Mix flour and salt well.
Add water and mix.
Knead and then roll out.
Cut out desired shapes and figurines.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool;	paint with acrylic paint and then varnish.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots until almost done, not overcooked, fork-tender. Bring remaining ingredients to a boil (everything but the carrots).
Pour over carrots and chill.

title: tanner's meat loaf
directions: Wash hands with soap and water.
Using your hands, mix together well
the ground beef, eggs, Lipton onion soup, bread, and ketchup.
Shape into a loaf, and put into a 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Take out and add my famous sauce.

title: chicken on the bun
directions: Saute chicken, pepper, celery, onion and seasoning in melted butter or oleo.
When thoroughly heated and slightly browned, add evaporated milk and mix.
Remove from heat; cool and add chopped eggs and mayonnaise.
Spread on open half of bun.
Top with shredded cheese.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve. Then reheat at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mother's fabulous fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in a big glass bowl. Microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High.
Stir once or twice. Remove from microwave. Stir in a 6-ounce package (1 cup) semi-sweet chocolate, 1 cup pecans and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir well. Pour into a buttered dish.

title: golden jam
directions: Soak apricots in water to barely cover overnight.
In the morning, add pineapple juice, ground orange and lemon juice. Measure cup for cup, fruit and sugar.
Boil slowly until thick. Put in sterile jars.

title: puffy cheese bake
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 4 triangles.
Line bottom and sides of buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with bread triangles. (For a crown effect, place 8 triangles upright against sides of dish.
Arrange remaining triangles in bottom of dish.)
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Cook uncovered in 350° oven until puffed and golden brown, about 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in skillet and add steak, onion and garlic.
Cook until meat is brown but not crisp.
Add green pepper and bouillon. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes. Mix cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on rice or chow mein noodles.

title: pizza rice skillet
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Add zucchini and onion and cook, stirring, until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in boiling water, rice and Italian seasoning.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer about 20 minutes, until rice is almost tender.
Spread pizza sauce evenly over rice, then arrange salami slices on top.
Sprinkle with mushrooms, olives and cheese.
Cover skillet and cook over medium heat about 5 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions, making two 8-inch layers.
Bake and cool; split layers horizontally after they cool. Blend together sugar, sour cream and coconut; chill.
Spread all but 1 cup onto three layers of cake.
Blend the remaining 1 cup with the Cool Whip and spread on top layer and sides.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days.
Important:
Do not leave unrefrigerated for long period.

title: mandarin orange torte
directions: Mix the ingredients; beat for 2 or 3 minutes.
Butter an 8 x 8-inch pan or a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in batter.
Prepare topping.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box; chill.
Cook until thick the sugar, salt, beaten eggs, 2 tablespoons flour and the juice from the pineapple and oranges.
Pour over macaroni and set in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, add pineapple, mandarin oranges and cherries.
Add cherry juice for color.
Add Cool Whip.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids and stir until mixed.
Cook on low heat until dough is stiff, stirring often.
Put on floured surface and allow to cool.
Knead as you would bread dough.
Store in airtight container.
Provides great fun for kids and a good stress release for adults (especially nursing students!).

title: saucy meat loaves
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and 1/2 cup tomato sauce in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well; shape into 6 individual meat loaves. Place in a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine 1/2 cup tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and water; mix well. Pour over meat loaves.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar and flour; stir in reserved juice.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: candy trifles
directions: *May use chocolate, butterscotch, caramel or peanut butter.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce, beans and green chilies.
Layer half of tortillas on bottom of 12 x 8-inch pan.
Spread half of meat mixture over; sprinkle with half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; let stand 10 minutes.
Or, cook in microwave at full power for 16 to 18 minutes, or until heated through.
Turn 3 to 4 times during cooking time.

directions: Make yellow Duncan
Hines cake according to directions. Bake in a 11 1/2 x 17
x
1-inch pan.
Leave cake in pan. Combine cream cheese,
milk and vanilla instant pudding.
Beat until creamy; spread on
cooled cake.
Do not overbeat mixture too long as it
will
stiffen.
Then

Then

Cool
Whip. Sprinkle with coconut or nuts for topping.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
With a nonstick cooking spray, spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Taking 1 can of the crescent rolls, press the seams together and line the bottom of the dish.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Add pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jo mazzoti
directions: Cook together onions, fat and ground pork until browned.
Add tomato paste, water and other ingredients (except noodles). Simmer 15 minutes to make rich sauce.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk and lemonade together until thick.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and place in refrigerator until set.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together the powdered sugar, peanut butter, brown sugar and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Put in ungreased pan (9 x 13-inch). Melt together 1/4 cup butter and the chocolate chips; spread on top.
Chill well.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain and reserve juice from cherries and pineapple.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to juice and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Dissolve Jell-O in this and add Cokes.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour into baking dish and refrigerate.

title: valentine's float
directions: Put large scoop of ice cream in a large tall glass.
Put in a small amount of soda; mix just a little, so you still have pieces of ice cream floating in it.
Pour in soda to fill the glass.
Use a butter knife or spoon to make a slit in a marshmallow just deep enough to hold a cherry that you push inside.
With a spoon, set the marshmallow on top of your float.
Serve with straws.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and pour into large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Lightly coat casserole dish with nonstick spray and add mixture.
Top with additional cheese, if desired.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tomato french dressing
directions: Blend in your blender or use mixer until creamy and smooth.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients	together and cut in shortening. Mix with
warm	water.	Turn
out
and	knead 5 minutes until smooth and
elastic.
Let	stand
in bowl 30 minutes covered. Roll
out to	18
x 6-inch rectangle.
Cut in 3-inch squares. Put oil
in deep,
heavy
pan.	Heat to 375°.
Fry a few at a time,
being careful not to crowd them during cooking.
These will
puff
and you
tear off a corner and fill with honey or syrup or whatever you like and eat.

title: german chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix with evaporated milk and melted butter.
Pat 2/3 in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray on the bottom only.
Bake for 6 minutes in a 350° oven.
Melt caramels with evaporated milk on low heat.
Sprinkle desired amount of chocolate chips on cake mix when removed from oven.
Spread caramel mixture over chips.
Dot with rest of cake mix.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: korean chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into large baking dish.
(Save about 1 cup mixture.)
Marinate chicken in this mixture overnight. Cook chicken on grill, brushing often with extra mixture.

title: fruitcake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients. Beat the eggs well with the sugar.
Pour into cake mix with fruit and nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 280° for 1 hour or until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and salt.
Beat well; stir together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture; stir in bananas and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: crabmeat stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; mash.
Remove any cartilage from crabmeat; break meat into small pieces.
Combine crabmeat, egg yolks, celery, mustard, salt and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Stuff whites with mixture and sprinkle with paprika.

title: beef tater bake
directions: Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove and drain grease. Combine 3 cups hot, mashed potatoes and 3/4 cup shredded cheese. Spread on meat mixture.
Top with 1/4 cup shredded cheese.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Stir in butterscotch morsels and continue to use mixer.
Pour batter into 9 x 12-inch cake pan and put more morsels onto top of cake.
Bake at 350° until cake is done.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Combine and bring to a full boil stirring constantly sugar, milk, salt, marshmallow cream and margarine.
Boil 5 minutes over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in until melted, chocolate morsels.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: california garden casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir ground beef, green pepper, onion and celery in 10-inch skillet until beef is light brown; drain.
Stir in noodles, sauce mix and water.
Heat to boiling and pour into ungreased baking dish 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 to 5 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Place in pot and cover with water.
Add about 1 tsp. salt to water.
Bring to boil, cover, and simmer about 15 minutes until soft when stuck with a fork.
Drain and let cool on cutting board.
When cool, cut into 1/2 inch squares and place in large bowl.
Add finely diced, cooled, hard-boiled eggs.
Mix with fork.
Sprinkle with all four seasonings and stir, then season lightly again and stir.
Begin adding mayonnaise a large spoonful at a time until all potatoes are well coated. Spoon into serving bowl.
Shred cheese slices over potato salad. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken curry
directions: *Available in most Oriental stores.

title: rose's cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage in large skillet.
Put water, margarine and seasoning and let come to a boil.
Add cabbage and diced sausage along with shredded apple and onion.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes, until tender.

title: barbecued bologna
directions: Score meat in diamond shape. Stick whole cloves in meat at intervals.
Place on rack in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine sugar, mustard, vinegar and orange rind.
At the end of 30 minutes cooking period, baste bologna.
Then again every 10 to 15 minutes for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: 22 minute cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large bowl.
Do not use mixer. In a saucepan, combine margarine, water, shortening and cocoa; bring to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to batter and blend thoroughly.
Pour into 12 x 18-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender. Stir in sauce mix, tomatoes and tomato paste; simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine meat sauce and noodles; mix lightly.
Layer with cheese in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add cocoa and food coloring.
Add salt, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Alternately add soda and vinegar.
Blend; do not beat hard.
Bake at 350°.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Add this just before serving.

title: honey buttered popcorn
directions: Keep the popcorn warm.
Combine butter and honey; mix well. Drizzle over popcorn; add nuts.
Stir or shake until evenly coated.
Spread the mixture in a thin layer on a lightly buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Break apart when cool.

title: jalapeno black-eyed pea and rice casserole
directions: Brown onions and ground beef together.
Stir in peas, rice and tomatoes; mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: heavenly potato casserole
directions: Melt cheese and mayonnaise over low heat.
Stir often.
When cheese is melted, pour over partially thawed potatoes.
Bake in greased, oblong pan for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Put crumbled bacon on top for last 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix pineapple juice and mashed potatoes; beat until smooth. Using one marshmallow for a center, form balls of sweet potato around marshmallow.
Roll in crushed cornflakes until well coated. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Peel onions and cut small slice from top and bottom.
Slice each onion into 6 wedges, cutting to within 1/2-inch of bottom. Set aside.
Prepare stuffing mix by directions on package. Cool. Stir in cheese.
Fill onions with mixture.
Wrap each onion in aluminum foil. Place in a 13 x 9 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spiced tea
directions: To water, add cloves and cinnamon.
Heat to boiling.
Add tea; cover and set for ??? minutes.
Drain.
Heat orange juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Stir.
Add to hot tea.
Serve and enjoy on a cold night.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: caviar spread
directions: Chop eggs very fine.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Spread on bottom of lightly greased spring-form pan.
Spread onions (finely chopped) on top of eggs.
Mix cream cheese with 2/3 cup of sour cream and spread over onions with a wet spatula.
Chill in refrigerator overnight or a minimum of 3 hours.
Just before serving, spread caviar (drain liquid) over top.
Remove spring circle (leave on bottom of pan).
Use remaining sour cream to "ice" sides.
Use parsley and thinly sliced lemon to decorate. Serve with rye cocktail rounds or rye or wheat crackers.

title: lefse
directions: Mix together and divide into balls.
Roll out and bake on lefse grill until done.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Beat together the sugar, pumpkin, oil and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add and beat until smooth.
Blend in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: vivian's sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and margarine well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Add sour cream and flour; beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat 5 minutes.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: old-fashioned soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Then mix in the buttermilk to which the soda has been added.
Mix well.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Roll out onto a floured pastry cloth or table until dough is about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out desired shapes with cookie cutters. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly browned. Overbaking makes them crisp.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green chilies; season with garlic and onion powder and pepper.
Drain well.
Add 1 can cream of chicken and 1/4 can of water.
In deep casserole dish, layer as follows:
tortilla chips, meat mixture, grated cheese.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Add a little milk to last layer and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Day before:
In large kettle, place shin beef with bone, water, salt and beans.
Bring to boil, skim, cover and simmer 3 hours.
In oil, saute garlic, onion, parsley, ground beef and pepper until onion is tender, discard garlic.
Remove bone from soup, cut off meat.
Add meat to soup along with onion mixture, celery, cabbage, carrots and tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Refrigerate.
About 30 minutes before serving, skim fat from soup.
Bring soup slowly to a boil.
Add spaghetti, zucchini and peas.
Cook, covered, about 10 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with grated Parmesan or Romano cheese.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Add eggs. Sift dry ingredients together and mix with buttermilk. Add to first mixture. Fold in nuts, prunes and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured angel food or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: frosted party ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well; chill.
Shape into ball.
Cream cream cheese and milk; blend well.
Frost ball.

title: stuffed tomatoes with tuna
directions: Combine all; spoon into tomatoes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add chicken broth, carrots, potatoes, green beans, parsley, tarragon and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve with 5 crackers.

title: cucumber sandwich
directions: Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry dressing; spread on bread.
Slice cucumber; place on top.
Sprinkle on dill weed.

title: leek and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan.
Add milk and salt.
Cover and cook until slightly tender, about 10 minutes.
Arrange layers of potatoes and the leeks in a 5-cup casserole or baking dish. Combine crumbs, butter and white pepper and sprinkle over the top. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken spoon bread
directions: Combine corn meal, milk and chicken broth.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Add beaten egg yolks, salt, baking powder, shortening and chicken.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cornmeal mixture.
Turn into greased baking dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve at once with chicken gravy.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown hamburg and onion together; spread in bottom of greased casserole.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
In blender, mix milk, Bisquick and eggs for 1 minute.
Pour over mixture in casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour or until a knife comes out clean.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; scoop out the center and chop. Cook squash halves in lightly salted water in covered large pot about 15 minutes or until almost tender; drain.
In a skillet melt butter or margarine; add onion and ham and saute until onion is golden.
Stir in chopped squash and cook until tender.
Stir in next 3 ingredients and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Spoon into squash halves.
Place in a large shallow pan.
Pour water over bottom of pan.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle remaining parsley.

title: orange snowballs
directions: Mix and chill overnight, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Add milk, margarine and sugar into a pan and boil for 10 to 14 minutes (12 minutes seems good).
When boiling is done set onto a cold burner for a couple of minutes.
Then add Marshmallow Fluff, peanut butter, vanilla and flour.
Beat for a few minutes until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan. Does not need to be refrigerated.

title: lemon eclair dessert
directions: Layer one layer of crackers in an 11 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix pudding with milk; let stand until set.
Add jello; mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover first layer of crackers with 1/2 of filling.
Add another layer of crackers.
Top with last of filling; end with last layer of crackers.
Spread lemon icing over crackers.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: lorie's lasagna
directions: Crumble hamburger meat in skillet and cook before adding it to simmering spaghetti sauce.
Start out with a layer of meat, then noodles, then cheeses (use generous amounts of cheeses, to your liking).
Bake in 325° oven until hot and bubbly, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Wash
rich
thoroughly	in
a strainer with cold water. Place rice
in a saucepan with 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat
to simmer.
Cook, covered, for 35 minutes or until
kernels are
tender.
Uncover
and
fluff with a fork. Drain
any	excess liquid.
Toss
cooked
rice
with	apples, celery,
brown sugar and lemon juice.
Combine dressing ingredients and mix with salad ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken leo
directions: Wrap bacon around chicken breasts.
Line casserole pan with dried chipped beef.
Lay chicken breasts on dried chipped beef. Mix mushroom soup and sour cream together.
Pour mixture over chicken breasts.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cover casserole with foil.
Good served over rice.

title: baked bread pudding
directions: Heat eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla until warm.
Crumble biscuits in dish.
Sprinkle flour over biscuits.
Pour liquid over biscuits.
Let set, covered, 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate lace cornucopias
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Microwave sugar, corn syrup and margarine in bowl on High for 2 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in chocolate until completely melted.
Gradually stir in flour and nuts until well blended.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Cook on medium heat until tortellini is tender.
Amounts of broth and tortellini may vary for your preference.

title: hot chicken appetizers
directions: Cut each wing in half and discard wing tips.
In shallow pan, combine eggs and undiluted juice concentrate.
In another pan, combine crumbs, pecans, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a shallow roasting pan.
Dip each chicken piece in egg mixture, then roll in crumbs.
Put in pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Turn once during baking.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Rinse and drain sauerkraut; sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cocoa.
Snip sauerkraut into small pieces.
Cream butter until fluffy; add eggs one at a time and add sugar.
Cream until light and add vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with water.
(Begin with flour and end with flour).
Fold in sauerkraut.
Turn batter into 2 (8-inch) round layer pans.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat tomato soup just to boiling while you are dissolving gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Pour soup and gelatin, mixed, over softened cream cheese and mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Use wire whisk; do not use mixer.
Pour into mold that has been well rubbed with mayonnaise and refrigerate until jelled.
Serve with crackers.

title: jello pudding banana cake
directions: Mash bananas.
Add cake mix, pudding, eggs, water and oil. Mix, then add the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: mary raper's white raisin cake
directions: Cover raisins with water and cook until tender.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, raisin water and beaten eggs.
Add spices.
Add the raisins, well dredged in extra flour (not seeded raisins).
Bake in stem pan about 1 hour.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar until fluffy.
Gradually add flour. Roll dough on floured surface 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares or diamonds.
Prick cookies with fork.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove immediately to cool.

title: holiday pumpkin-pecan pie
directions: Combine 1 beaten egg, pumpkin, 1/3 cup sugar and pumpkin pie spice.
Spread on unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Combine the corn syrup, 2 beaten eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, margarine and vanilla; stir in pecans.
Spoon over pumpkin mix.
Bake in a 350°oven for 50 minutes, or until filling is set.
Cool on rack.

title: festive sweet potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.

title: date pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except egg whites.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put into buttered pan.
Set in pan of lukewarm water.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cream together potatoes, 1/2 of sharp cheese, sour cream, cream cheese and margarine.
Add salt and pepper.
Put in remaining cheese on top.
Cover.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and simmer until all is cooked, stirring occasionally.

title: "fast chili"
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Also good using cooked, diced chicken.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Dissolve Jello in 1 cup boiling water, set aside to cool.
In another bowl cream, the cream cheese with sugar and vanilla until smooth.
In large bowl whip Pet milk; add the cream cheese mixture mix, then add the Jello mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and keep in refrigerator 24 hours for best flavor.
Makes enough mixture to fill 9x13x2-inch dish.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach thoroughly, reserving 1/2 cup of the juice. Make thickening of butter, flour and juice by putting in small saucepan and bringing it to a slow boil. Remove thickening from heat and let it cool and mix with all the remaining ingredients. Bake at 450° for 45 minutes, uncovered, in a 13 x 9 pan. Serves 6 to 8.

title: whoppin' butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add flour and 1 cup crushed Whoppers at low speed.
Shape dough around individual whole malted milk balls (cover candy completely).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes or until cookies are set but not brown.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove to wire cooling rack; cool slightly, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to directions.
Spread cookie mix in 12-inch pizza pan and bake at 350° for 12 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks; add buttermilk and mix.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Place soda on top of mixture and pour hot water over it.
Mix thoroughly. Add stiffly beaten egg whites, leaving a lumpy appearance to batter.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Combine oats, vanilla and nuts in large bowl.
Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil. Pour chocolate mixture into oats mixture and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Yields about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: zucchini creole
directions: Peel zucchini; cut and put into pot with grease and other ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: danish style stuffed cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cut out core and cook cabbage in water to cover for 15 minutes to loosen outer leaves.
Cool in cold water.
Simmer rice in milk 30 minutes to form a creamy mixture.
Cool.
Mix meats, salt and rice mixture.
Add egg whites, one at a time, then pepper and onion. Filling is soft.
Carefully peel off 12 cabbage leaves; place on board.
Cut ribs to make leaves lie flat.
Place a heaping teaspoon of filling in center of each.
Roll up, folding in ends. Place seam side down in pan.
Pour broth around rolls.
Drop 1 teaspoon molasses on each.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes; turn rolls and baste.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Transfer rolls to a platter.
Ladle pan juices into skillet.
Bring to a boil. Combine cornstarch and cold water to make a paste.
Stir in cornstarch paste.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Serve sauce over rolls.

title: anything casserole
