directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam or grease with shortening or margarine.
Mix up all of the ingredients in another bowl.
Pour into casserole dish.
Put lid on or cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
If you have any extra cheese, sprinkle it on top.

title: french-canadian sugar pie i
directions: In a bowl, mix the egg yolks, sugar, maple syrup, milk and the butter.
In another bowl, mix the egg whites until they make firm peaks and incorporate into first mixture with a spatula.
You have to gently fold the egg whites to incorporate air in the mixture. Put the preparation in pie crust and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add 2 tablespoons milk and mix well. Add other ingredients. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Pour into baked deep-dish pie crust.

title: zesty cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage 8 minutes; set aside.
Brown hamburger with onion; set aside.
Cook the rice and set aside.
Grease large casserole dish.
Layer the rice, cabbage and hamburger.
Pour spaghetti sauce over all.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Soft bread crumbs in milk.
Add ground beef, onions, eggs and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly and shape into 1-inch meat balls. Melt butter in pan.
Add meat balls and brown on all sides. Remove meat balls from pan.
Stir flour into drippings and blend well.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water and gradually add to flour mixture, stirring constantly until smooth.
(Add Kitchen Bouquet for color.) Cook over low heat for 3 minutes.
Add meatballs to sauce and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, alternating with flour.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Heat oil and saut onion slowly. Add the garlic. Add the remaining ingredients. Bring to boiling. Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: lazy day casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain well. Place meat back in pan and add soup, water and rice. Cook for 10 minutes. Cut cabbage in bottom of casserole and place meat mixture over. Do not stir. Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 hours. Uncover last half hour. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cabbage and green peas
directions: Add all ingredients except peas in a covered pot and bring to boil.
Reduce heat; add peas.
Cover and cook until the cabbage is done, stirring occasionally.
Add more water if necessary.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Spread the chicken breast pieces on bottom of a casserole dish. Pour some dabs of margarine over it.
Sprinkle the onion soup mix over it.
Pour the cream mixture over it.
Bake it on 350° for about 45 minutes (it should be bubbling).
Sprinkle shoestring potatoes over it.
Serve over rice.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread and layer in pan with kidney beans and any raw vegetables that you like, onions, green peppers, cucumbers, cauliflower, peas, corn, etc.
Top with cheese.
Mix pickle juice and mayonnaise until thin.
Pour over top of layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: french style green beans
directions: Drain vegetables.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: cucumber pickles(per jar recipe)
directions: Add salt, sugar, pepper and spices to each jar of cucumbers that is being processed.
Pour vinegar to 2 inches from top of jar and remainder with water.
Install jar lids and boil in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Combine chili sauce and jelly in saucepan or chafing dish; heat on medium, stirring constantly until blended.
Add franks and heat through.
Serve warm.
Yields 60 franks.

title: crispy popcorn
directions: Spray large cookie sheet with nonstick coating. Melt chocolate and peanut butter together. Meanwhile in a very large bowl, combine popcorn, cereal and peanuts. Pour warm melted chocolate mixture over popcorn mixture, tossing to coat well. Spread on cookie sheet. Cool. Break into pieces. Store up to 5 days. Makes 22 cups.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Mix curry powder, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper. Pat chicken breasts dry. Sprinkle with and rub in spice mix. Combine 1/4 teaspoon salt with next 5 ingredients is large skillet. Arrange chicken over mix. Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Remove to serving plate; sprinkle with parsley.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and food coloring. Sift together flour, coconut and salt.
Alternate flour mixture with buttermilk into Crisco mixture.
Mix soda and vinegar and fold into batter.
Do not beat in.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: candied apples
directions: You will need 10 to 12 wooden sticks.

title: tom thumb pancakes
directions: Combine oil, eggs and milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour by tablespoon and bake on hot griddle. Makes 12 to 14.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, margarine, milk, cocoa and peanut butter in large boiler.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop onto wax paper.
Allow to cool completely before storing.

title: clam dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese with mayonnaise; add all remaining ingredients.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: stitzers delight
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Batter will be very stiff.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon on cookie sheet for each cookie on slightly greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Purchase chicken-flavor bouillon in cube or envelope form.

title: country meat loaf
directions: Mix chuck, onion, bread crumbs, egg, sour cream, ketchup, mustard, parsley, salt and pepper in a large bowl; mix well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Spread evenly and press down.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Melt
margarine,
then
add sugar and other ingredients. Bake 25 to
30 minutes at 350° in spoonfuls or in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: baked chicken yum! yum!
directions: Clean fat and gristle off chicken.
Roll chicken in Ragu sauce, then roll in italian bread crumbs.
Spray baking pan or cookie sheet with baking spray.
Bake in oven on at least 400 degrees until done.
Spray chicken from time to time with butter spray so it will be crispy.
It's that easy!

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake; cut into bite-size pieces.
Place in bottom of large punch bowl.
Make puddings and pour over cake.
Crush candy bars in blender.
Pour 3/4 over pudding.
Pour Cool Whip over candy bars.
Sprinkle with remaining candy bars.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and margarine; cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in flavorings.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: aunt dawson's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs, oil and water.
Add flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and soda; mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans (or in large Bundt pan or may use 3 or 4 one pound coffee cans.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
If using coffee cans, they will bake faster.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar.
Melt butter in glass measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Add butter and milk to yeast mixture.
Slowly add flour until dough is ready to knead.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° until lightly brown, approximately 12 minutes.

title: all season bread
directions: *This can be shredded apples, shredded sweet potato or 2 medium zucchini (shredded), to make 2 cups.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: In a large pot brown the beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add potatoes, peas and carrots, soup base, water, salt and pepper to meat mixture.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Blend 1 cup of the milk with the flour. Add to soup, along with remaining milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese; heat and stir just until cheese melts.

title: vanilla chip lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, stir together 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup granulated sugar; with pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture onto bottom of 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until slightly browned.
Remove from oven; sprinkle vanilla chips over crust.
In medium bowl, stir together egg substitute, lemon juice, lemon peel, remaining 1/4 cup flour and remaining 3/4 cup sugar; carefully pour over chips and crust.
Bake 15 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly in pan on wire rack; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Yield:
About 3 dozen bars.

title: orange julius
directions: Prepare in blender until consistency of thick milkshake. Serve in iced glasses immediately.
Makes 3 cups.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vinegar.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Add milk slowly.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 layers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add egg, beating well.
Add oil and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to first mixture and beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Roll into long rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper; put in refrigerator or freeze to chill.
Slice in thin slices.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple jam
directions: Cook pineapple and sugar together for 20 minutes.
Add Karo and syrup; heat to boiling point.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: baked chili con queso
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Salt chopped onion.
Place colander inside mixing bowl.
Chop tomatoes with pastry cutter or knife, letting juice fall into bowl.
Add chilies to tomatoes and stir. Place chilies and tomatoes in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add onion and cheese.
Bake until cheese melts (about 1 hour).
Baking can be sped up by preheating in microwave.
Dip or spoon mixture onto tortilla chips or pita bread and top with sour cream.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Put apples and sugar in bowl; let stand for 10 minutes or longer.
Add oil, egg (lightly beaten) and vanilla.
Mix well. Combine dry ingredients and add to apple mixture, mixing well. Add raisins and nuts.
Grease well the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour mixture into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with Butter Sauce.

title: kielbasa and pineapple
directions: Cut kielbasa into bite size pieces and put in crock-pot. Heat the pineapple juice and melt in the brown sugar. Remove from heat. Blend in the chili sauce. Cook on high for 1 1/2 hours. Add pineapple chunks.

title: holiday house fragrance
directions: This is an on-the-top-of-the-stove or potpourri pot simmering fragrance (not edible).

title: jan's sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream butter. Combine flour, baking soda, salt and sugar. Add all dry ingredients plus vanilla. Roll out cookies on floured surface. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: toasting crackers
directions: Roll thin and sprinkle salt over top.
Cut in squares, then bake.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Heat milk and melt marshmallows in milk on low heat; add cream cheese and stir well until cheese is melted.
Add cottage
cheese and drained pineapple.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions and add to mixture; add chopped nuts and diced cherries.
Reserve cherries to garnish on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread nuts on bottom of pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Spread coconut over nuts.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together; add confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pie by mama lois
directions: Wet all ingredients with 1/2 cup milk.
Stir 1/2 stick margarine into mixture.
Beat 3 egg yolks and stir into mixture. Then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Use egg whites for meringue with 1 tablespoon sugar for each white.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Blend with first mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta pesto florentine
directions: In food processor or blender, combine walnuts and garlic; process until finely chopped.
Add spinach, cheese, corn oil, salt and basil; process until well blended.
(For thinner sauce, gradually add a few tablespoons water.) Spoon over linguine; toss to coat.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook hamburger and chopped onion until well done.
Let cool. Mix together the hamburger, both cheeses and sour cream. Cook jumbo shells on medium heat just until shells are workable (able to stuff without breaking).
Do not cook until they are completely done. Remove from heat. Run under cold water so they stop cooking and do not stick together.
Stuff mixture into shells and put into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Put into oven at 350°.
Cook until sauce begins to boil. Remove and eat.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and butter in pan over low heat.
Boil, remove and add Rice Krispies until coated.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix peanut butter, fudge and syrup, spread over bottom mixture.
Then spread on ice cream, then fudge, then freeze.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake by box directions and make 4 round cakes.

title: grilled teriyaki chicken
directions: 1. Place flour in zip lock bag. Add breasts. Shake until breasts are covered with flour. Dip in bowl filled with
soy sauce until completely soaked.
2. Place one side of grill on low heat. Leave other side
off. Breasts should be placed on the side that is off.
3. Baby the breasts every 5 minutes. Close lid, come back
in 5 minutes and turn again. Continue this until done.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer chicken in 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Spread soup over top of chicken.
Cube cheese and place on top of soup.
Sprinkle Doritos on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese and soup are hot and bubbly.

title: "new potatoes"
directions: Clean potatoes. Cut up or peel around the center of the potatoes. Steam until done. Add margarine or butter. Add parsley flakes and salt and pepper, if desired.

title: "preach" cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all dry ingredients together. Add milk.
Pour over butter.
Drop in peaches.
Don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Then beat in eggs.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tortellini with shrimp
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions; keep warm. In a large skillet, melt butter.
Saute onion and garlic 3 minutes.
Add shrimp; saute 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, ham, peas, and grated cheese; cook 1 minute.
Toss with tortellini; sprinkle with shredded cheese.
If desired, garnish with fresh basil.

title: chicken breast
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with dried beef.
Place chicken breasts, wrapped in bacon strips, on beef.
Mix in separate bowl the sour cream, cream cheese and chicken soup.
Pour mixture over chicken; cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.
Uncover last few minutes to brown.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: easy beef-n-rice
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil; lower the heat and simmer until tender, about 35 to 40 minutes.
In large frying pan, saute the ground beef.
Drain off any excess fat, then add puree and seasoning.
Add the cooked rice.
Heat through and serve.

title: 10 minute peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in 2-quart casserole or mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts. Microwave 3 to 5 minutes (3 1/2 minutes) on High.
Stir after 3 minutes until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda until light and fluffy.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness on large, well-buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and crack.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix and bake in a casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Add lemon juice to sour milk; set 5 minutes.
Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat with mixer until blended.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mix the two mixtures together.
Stir in diced zucchini.
Spoon batter into 9 x 12-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
No frosting needed.

title: boboli appetizer
directions: *Such as cucumber, broccoli, green onion, green and red pepper and radishes.

title: basic soup mix
directions: To serve, boil 4 cups water.
Add 3/4 cup soup mix.
Simmer until vegetables are cooked.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Add together all ingredients and heat slowly in a crock-pot or on the stove.
Adjust sugar and spice amounts to taste.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for 10 minutes until brown.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Cream well.
Add flour gradually; mix.
Add nuts.
Chill.
Roll small pieces of dough in palm of hand to form a ball or crescent 2 to 2 1/2 inches long and 1/2-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes (bottoms brown).
While warm roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: warm broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on the package and drain well.
Saute onion in small amount of butter or oleo.
Add remaining ingredients and melt over low heat.
Serve warm with wide corn chips.

title: fourth of july pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir until thick.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Arrange fruit on top; refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: 22 minutes chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Mix oleo, water, Crisco and cocoa in pan and bring to boil.
Pour hot mix over flour and sugar.
Mix buttermilk, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: cornish hens in dutch oven
directions: Put butter or oil in hot Dutch oven and fry the birds, turning them until browned on all sides.
Add parsley, green pepper, garlic and onion.
When these are tender, add wine.
Cover the oven and simmer over low coals.
In a few minutes, add the tomato sauce, mushrooms and seasonings.
Simmer slowly for 1 1/2 hours. Good dish to serve over noodles.

title: veggie bites
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Brush bottom of rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) with 1 tablespoon melted margarine.

title: great northern beans
directions: Soak beans in 2 quarts of lukewarm water for 1/2 hour. Add all the other ingredients and cook over medium heat, adding more water when necessary. Serve with cornbread and Collard Greens.

title: mint julep
directions: *Made of 2 cups sugar and 1 cup water, boiled 3 minutes and chilled.

title: gran-gran's banana punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Let cool.
Mix juices and syrup together.
Mash bananas to a pulp.
Stir mashed bananas into juice.
Freeze, stirring occasionally, until mushy hard or freeze until ready to use.
When ready to use, thaw until mushy.
Mix with ginger ale.
Serves 20 to 30.

title: banana chocolate chip bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, egg and butter together in a large bowl.
Beat until fluffy.
Set aside.
Combine bananas and milk in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Stir by hand into creamed mixture, alternately with banana mixture until flour is just moistened. Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Grease 1 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pan.
Turn batter into pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cook in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Heat
the
bacon
grease
in an iron pot until smoking. Stir in	flour
and
make
a
dark brown roux by stirring over medium heat
about
minutes.
Add chopped onions and bell pepper and cook
until
limp.	Heat
10 cups water in a large pot, then
add roux mixture to pot.
Add all other ingredients except seafood and file powder. Simmer at least 3 hours.
Add shrimp 20 minutes before serving and oysters and crabmeat 5 to 10
minutes
before serving.
Serve
in
bowls	over rice and sprinkle with file powder.

title: spider corncake
directions: Sift cornmeal, flour and soda together; add sour milk, eggs, 1 c. sweet milk and sugar and mix.
In heavy, shallow baking dish melt 1 Tbsp. butter.
Pour in batter.
Over top pour 1 c. sweet milk.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cut in wedges.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix wet.
Mix dry.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool before removing from pans.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Chicken or turkey could be substituted.

title: beef casserole
directions: Put in casserole in layers.
Pour soup, milk and onions over the layers.
Bake for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serve over noodles. Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and chop. Set aside.
Pour oil in large mixing bowl. Add sugar and eggs. Beat well. Gradually add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Gently add apples.
Flour nuts lightly and add to cake mixture. Bake in cake pan or 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Glaze while warm with glaze.

title: glarch
directions: Mix the school glue, starch and food coloring in a disposable 1-pint plastic container and stir.
Knead the mixture on a newspaper-covered surface until smooth (a couple of minutes).
If it sticks to your hands, add a teaspoon of starch.
If it's too stringy, add 1/2 teaspoon glue.
Glarch doesn't store well, so it should be used the day it is made.

title: creamy beef and onions(low-fat)
directions: In skillet, cook ground turkey, mushrooms, onions and garlic until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Drain off fat.
In a bowl, mix gravy, yogurt, Worcestershire sauce, sage and pepper. Stir into meat mixture and heat.
Serve over noodles or rice. Makes 4 servings.
Very easy and very good.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine flour, powdered sugar and butter.
Press into a 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: brownies ala annie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and follow instructions on box. Don't worry about putting mayonnaise in brownies.
It
may sound strange but it's good.
Don't believe me, do you?
Well, fine. Make them and bring them to me.
I'll eat them.
Makes 10 to 12 big pieces.

title: crock pot roast
directions: Peel and cut potatoes and put in bottom of crock pot.
Salt roast with seasoned salt and garlic.
Place on top of potatoes. Peel and cut carrots and place in crock pot.
Mix soup mix and mushroom soup together and spread on top.
Cook on medium for approximately 8 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and serve with crackers or hollow out loaf of bread.

title: oat-pecan burgers
directions: Place all ingredients except rolled oats in a large saucepan. Stir well and bring to a slow boil over medium-low heat.
Stir in rolled oats and immediately remove from heat.
Cover and set aside to cool.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Form oat mixture into 2-inch patties and place in baking sheets (spray with Pam).
Bake for 15 minutes on each side.
Makes approximately 20 burgers.
Can serve with gravy.
Can freeze.

title: pozole #1
directions: In a large pot, put enough water to cover pork and hominy. Place garlic (whole cloves) in pot. Bring to boil, then reduce heat to medium and continue cooking until cooked. Add the seasonings. Cook 5 minutes more, stirring frequently to blend flavors. Serve with sliced radishes, diced onions, chopped lettuce, a dash of oregano or lemon and salt for extra flavor. Can also be served with tostadas. Serves 2 to 4.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat together the egg, cinnamon and sugar.
One and one-half pounds mixed nuts (as desired).
Coat nuts in liquid mixture and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 1/2 hour at 300° stirring every 10 minutes.
(I spray cookie sheet with Pam.)

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa. Add milk and margarine. Bring to a boil on medium heat, stirring occasionally. Cook 1 1/2 minutes or until a soft-ball stage is formed. Add vanilla, quick oats and peanut butter. Blend well and spoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk.
Heat on the stove over medium heat for 1 minute, then stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Let set for 3 minutes then stir in oatmeal.
Then drop on a cookie sheet with a tablespoon.

title: treasures cheese ball
directions: Mix together cheese and dates.
Form into a ball.
Roll in almonds.

title: bean soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Divide into 1 1/2 cup portions. Makes about 14 or 15 portions.

title: island chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir well.
Place chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brush on half of marmalade mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 minutes, basting occasionally with the remaining marmalade mixture.
Spoon pineapple chunks and orange sections over chicken; bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut up the candy, dates and pecans; cream sugar and butter. Add 1 egg at a time and mix well.
Add 1/2 flour with salt and soda and buttermilk to mixture.
Roll orange slices, pecans and dates in balance of flour.
Add coconut and fruit to batter.
Mix well. Bake at 250° until done (approximately 2 1/2 hours) in a greased and floured pan.

title: minestrone casserole
directions: Brown beef in large skillet; drain off fat; saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring mixture to boil and pour into a large casserole.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese just before serving.

title: pink fluff fruit salad
directions: Drain the canned fruit; mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a large, shallow baking pan, combine pumpkin seeds, sauce, butter and salt.
Bake about 2 hours, stirring occasionally or until seeds are crisp, dry and golden brown.

title: mahogany cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Add cold water and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cocoa together; then combine with first ingredients.
Add hot water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been lightly greased and floured.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat
oven on 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Then add zucchini and pecans.
This makes a lot of batter, so either use two greased loaf pans or one greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut 3 hot dogs in half.
Remove 3 crescent rolls from tube and cut each in half.
Wrap half a crescent roll around each hot dog half.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve with catsup and mustard for dipping.

title: grape-picker potatoes
directions: Line cast-iron skillet with bacon.
Layer thin sliced potatoes and sliced Swiss or crumbled Feta and green onions.
Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Dot last layer with margarine.
Cook 5 minutes on top of stove.
Cover and cook 45 minutes in a 425° oven.
Turn off and let sit in hot oven for 15 minutes.
Reverse onto platter after draining off grease.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water.
Peel and dice.
Dice bacon, then fry crisp.
Put bacon and chopped onions together with the potatoes.
Set aside.

title: quick mix one egg cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease bottom of 8-inch square or 9-inch round cake pan.
Place margarine in mixing bowl.
Add all the dry ingredients; don't mix.
Add the milk and vanilla.
Stir just until mixed.
Beat 150 strokes by hand or 1 minute with electric mixer.
Scrape bowl.
Add egg and beat the same amount again.
Pour into pan.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle on topping.
Return to oven 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in boiling water until done.
While chicken is cooking, prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Set aside.
When chicken is done, shred or chop into chunks.
Reserve chicken broth for later.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Tear into small pieces. Save broth.
Combine chicken, soup and broth together.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour chicken mixture into pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, pepper, melted margarine and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Cut batter into chicken with spoon until mixed through.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Place beans in 6-quart pan.
Cover. Heat to boiling.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Allow to stand 1 hour.
Heat again to boiling point.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook until beans are tender 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
In a large skillet, brown beef, onion, green peppers and garlic.
Drain off excess fat.
Add meat mixture to beans.
Stir in all the rest of the ingredients.
Bring everything to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer about 1/2 to 1 hour.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: baked green beans
directions: Mix and cook ingredients in saucepan.
Fill empty can of mushroom soup and add to rest of ingredients and cook until thickened.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Slice unpeeled zucchini.
Place in a large saucepan with onion.
Add chicken stock.
Add dill weed and cover.
Cook for 30 minutes, or until vegetables are soft.
Remove from heat and mash well.
Add cream.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Bake cake; let cool.
Poke holes in cake.
Put sliced bananas on top of cake.
Pour pudding mix on cake.
Chill and serve.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: Beat butter, granulated sugar and vanilla in large bowl until fluffy. Add flour and walnuts; beat on low speed of mixer until well blended. Cover; refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until dough is firm enough to handle.

title: frozen chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine crushed wafers and melted butter.
Pat into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add butter and sugar.
Then add buttermilk, flour and extracts.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin loaf
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, pumpkin and Wesson oil.
Mix well.
Sift flour.
Measure and add all other ingredients, except raisins and nuts, to flour, then add to the first mixture.
Mix very well, then add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Makes 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In large mixing bowl combine all ingredients; blend well. Store in tightly covered container.
Yields 3 3/4 cups mix, about fifteen 6-ounce servings.

title: baked blintzes
directions: Melt enough margarine to coat rectangular Pyrex baking dish (8 x 11-inch).
Place frozen blintzes in dish in one layer.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over blintzes.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake one hour at 375° until puffy and golden brown.
Can serve hot or at room temperature.

title: montine's fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour either into a Bundt pan or loaf pans.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pie filling, almond extract and eggs.
Mix by hand until ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes, turning once or twice during cooking.
Test for doneness with toothpick. The top should be somewhat moist when done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
(To bake in plastic or glass Bundt pan, add 2 minutes to cooking time.)
Let stand for 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: seashell tuna salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine Miracle Whip, lemon juice, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Stir in seashells, tuna, celery seed, onion and green pepper.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Put blueberry, cherry or strawberry pie filling on top of mixture or whatever you like best.
Chill. Makes 2 pies.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Drain vegetables and blot dry on paper towel.
Sprinkle equal amount of remaining ingredients on top of cream cheese.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes at 450° for 1 hour.
Bake the potatoes unwrapped to prevent tearing when scooping out.
Cut the baked potato in half (longways), and scoop out the potato.
Mix the potato, margarine and sour cream together until creamy.
Add the bacon, chives, pepper and salt.
Spoon the potato mixture back into the potato shells.
Return to a 350° oven for 20 or 25 minutes.
Add cheese slices to the potato tops to melt.
Enjoy!

title: hearty ham salad
directions: Combine and mix well all ingredients.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving. Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: polish doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Add 2 cups flour.
Let stand in warm place 1/2 hour.
Then beat eggs, sugar, vanilla, grated rind and salt until light.
Add this to the sponge.
Melt butter and add also to the sponge.
Add 5 cups flour.
Cover and let rise about 1 hour or until double in bulk.
Turn on floured board and pat with hands or roll until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter and let rise until light.
Drop in hot fat and fry until done.
These are very light and do not absorb grease.
(Sponge means the yeast, milk and flour mixture.)

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix together well in a casserole dish the first 8 ingredients (everything but eggs, milk and vanilla).
Bread should be torn into small pieces.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: caribbean chicken
directions: Prepare seasoning; shake chicken in bag to coat with seasoning mixture.
Heat oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken; stir-fry about 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 4 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Serve chicken mixture over rice.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Shake oil, sugar, vinegar, parsley, dash of pepper and dash of red pepper in a jar.
Refrigerate.

title: good fruitcake
directions: Cut nuts and fruits into fine pieces.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in well-greased (with butter) pan.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 1/2 hours, next day.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Cut thin, lengthwise slice from each potato; scoop out inside, leaving a thin shell.
Mash potatoes until no lumps remain.
Beat in milk, adding slowly just until potatoes are smooth and fluffy. Add butter, salt and pepper.
Beat vigorously until fluffy.

title: blue cheese bread spread
directions: Blend cheese and butter together until smooth.
Spread on bread slices.
Broil until spread turns brown and bubbly.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Add topping, then chill at least 4 hours.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook meat; drain. Add onion, carrots and chestnuts. Cook in skillet until tender. Add garlic, pepper and soy sauce. Allow meat mixture to cool completely. Wrap 2 tablespoons in wrapper; follow directions on package on how to wrap egg rolls, then dip finger in raw egg that has been beaten to seal the wrapper.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix 1 cup of warm water with the Jell-O and set aside to cool. Grind on the food chopper cranberries, lemon and orange; add sugar, chopped apples, celery and nuts.
Mix all in Jell-O and place in refrigerator until it is jelled.

title: crab swiss bites
directions: Combine crab, onion, cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and mix well.
Divide English muffin halves into quarters. Place on foil covered baking sheet.
Spoon on crab mixture and top with a few water chestnuts (slices).
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes or under broiler until cheese melts.

title: snap crackle popcorn and nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put corn and nuts in large open roasting pan.
Prepare caramel coating.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat sugar, margarine, syrup and salt to boiling. Boil 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove saucepan from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour hot mixture over popcorn and nuts, stirring to coat well.
Bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Spoon onto waxed paper to cool, stirring occasionally to separate.
Store in tightly covered containers to use within 1 week.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for
1 1/2 minutes. Start timing after mixture reaches a full boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter,
oats and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Then drop on waxed paper by teaspoonful.
Coconut or chopped nuts may be added if desired.

title: cheesy chicken crescent
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl, combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place about 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on wide end of each triangle and roll to opposite points.
In medium saucepan combine soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour half of soup mixture into ungreased 8 or 9-inch square dish. Arrange rolls over soup.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and return to oven an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: chocolate cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together pie filling and cornstarch until blended; pour into crust.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and extracts; pour evenly over pie filling.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until almost set in center.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Cover and refrigerate. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: In small amount of oil, brown the ground beef, chopped bell pepper and chopped onion.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.
Add tomato sauce and cooked rice.
Cut bell peppers in half if large or use whole small bell peppers with tops removed.
Scrape insides of peppers and precook slightly.
Fill with ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and allow cheese to melt.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, corn syrup, flour, salt and vanilla;
beat
well.
Stir
in
melted butter and pecans; mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: pepperoni sott'aceto, imbottiti(stuffed vinegar peppers)
directions: Core
each
cherry
pepper
by	carefully
cutting into center and
removing
the
stem
with
a	small, sharp knife. Remove the seeds from the peppers.
The best way to do this is to
insert your
index finger into the pepper and scrape them out.
Be sure to keep the peppers whole.	Set them aside.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: First bake a pie shell and when cold, fill with largest berries.
Make a glaze by mixing the sugar and cornstarch.
Add the liquid and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Cook until thick.
If not red enough, add a few drops of red coloring.
Let cool, then pour over berries in pie shell.
Let stand in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, top with whipped cream.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese, sour cream, instant pudding and then add pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Place in mold and chill.
Serves 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients well and shape into small balls, Bake for 15 minutes at 350, then bake for 15 minutes at 325.

title: lime cottage cheese salad-dessert
directions: Prepare
gelatin
with boiling water.
Add marshmallows and stir to melt.
Add lemon juice and set aside to cool until it starts
to thicken.
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese. Pour 1/2
of
mixture
into mold and place in refrigerator to chill. Put
other	half
into blender and blend until fluffy. Pour
over chilled
mixture and scatter nuts over top.
Chill until firm. Serve topped with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Measure warm water into a large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast. Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, margarine, egg and flour. Beat until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make stiff dough.
Cover bowl with aluminum foil tightly.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Divide into 32 pieces.
Roll each piece pencil shape 10-inches long.
Shape into pretzels.
Place on lightly greased sheets.
Blend together egg yolks and 2 tablespoons water.
Brush pretzels.
Sprinkle with coarse salt or sesame seed.
Let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in size, about 25 minutes.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes or until done.
Remove from sheets and cool on wire racks.

title: poor boy's
directions: Place meat and both mixes in slow cooker or 200° oven.
Cook all night or 8 hours.
Don't add any water.
After meat is done, shred and stir well.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Use the seasoning packet and bread crumbs for the stuffing mix and combine with the melted butter in a separate bowl.
Press about 1/2 this mixture into the bottom of the baking pan.
Remove the skin and bones from the cooked chicken and cut all chicken meat into bite sized pieces. Lay all the cooked chicken meat on top of the crumbs.
In another mixing bowl, combine the soups, the milk and the chicken broth and mix well.
Pour this mixture on top of the chicken.
Scatter the remainder of the crumb mixture over the top of the casserole. Place in a 350° oven and heat until hot and bubbly, approximately 45 minutes.
If you prefer only white meat, substitute cooked boneless chicken breast meat.
In a hurry?
Use canned chicken meat instead.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat the chicken broth to boiling.
Add salt, basil, thyme and rice. Reduce heat.
Cook, covered, until liquid is absorbed, about 45 minutes.

title: grilled vegetable medley
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Add squash, red pepper and zucchini; toss gently.
Arrange vegetables in a wire grilling basket coated with cooking spray.
Place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes or until tender, turning once.
Serves 6.

title: pecan sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle pecans and decorator sugars on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: easy applesauce bars
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Set aside.
Mix baking soda and applesauce together.
Then add to butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients and bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top. Yields 24 pieces.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In
medium
bowl,
combine
all ingredients; toss well. Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours.
Makes 6 servings, about 3/4 cup each.

title: easy chicken broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cook, covered, 30 minutes on 350°.
Remove lid and cook 10 minutes longer, uncovered.
May be prepared in advance. Yields 2 servings.

title: egg pie
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients in blender.
Soak bread in water. Squeeze water out and add to other ingredients.
Add vanilla. Pour in pie shell; bake in oven until brown, about 30 minutes, at 400°.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cheese biscuit
directions: Soften shortening, butter and cheese at room temperature. Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening and butter into flour; add cheese.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Roll, cut and bake at 450°.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Beat; add ingredients.
Bake in unbaked shell until center is firm at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: In a pan, place beans, corn and water chestnuts.
Spread mixture of sour cream, soup, onions and cheese over vegetables. Mix margarine, garlic salt, salt, pepper and crackers.
Spread over cheese mixture.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients until well blended (may not do well with hand mixer).
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour batter mixture in and smooth down with spatula.
Pour in apples (all if you like, but reserve a few for the top).
Pour in remaining batter and add the last few apples. Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Enjoy!

title: chili bake(low calorie)
directions: Brown meat in skillet with oil, salt, pepper, chili powder, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Add tomatoes and cook an additional 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni.
Pour mixture in casserole dish and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cover with grated cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook 5 minutes in pressure cooker; let stem return to down position, then add 1 small can of clams with broth.
Especially tasty with 1 can of Progresso white clam spaghetti sauce added along with the small can of clams.

title: creamed cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender.
Layer cauliflower, white sauce and cheese in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs until hot in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Tastes good.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Arrange bread slices on a baking sheet. Place a slice of cheese on each bread slice.
Place in oven to melt cheese.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart pot in hot oil, brown roast.
Spoon off fat. Stir in soups and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 2 hours. Add vegetables.
Cook 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Stir together flour and remaining 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Gradually stir into soup mixture. Cook
until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Pour cooked macaroni into dish; add margarine.
Beat eggs, adding salt, sugar, milk and cheese.
Pour over macaroni.
Bake in preheated oven to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until spoon inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Way bars in a little milk in boiler.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in ice cream maker.
Add milk to bring to fill line of container.

title: lime dressing
directions: Combine ingredients, mix until smooth.
Cover; chill 1 hour to blend flavors.
Serve with your favorite slices of fresh fruit or mix with canned tropical fruit salad.
Refrigerate unused dressing.
Yields approximately 3 cups.

title: old peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish or pan about 3 inches deep.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Top with peaches and juice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: curried artichoke salad
directions: Combine rice, broth, and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil and cook covered until done.
Empty rice into large bowl and cool. Add onions and olives.
Drain artichokes and combine marinade with curry powder and mayonnaise.
Add artichokes and toss with dressing.
Let stand refrigerated for a couple of hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and form into little balls. Cook on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread in even layer.
Spread dry cake mix onto cherry layer evenly.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Put butter slices over top.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flavors and buttermilk. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add German's chocolate that has been softened in warm oven.
Blend well.
Cook in 9-inch tube pan at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Place cake under a tight fitting cover while still hot and leave covered until cool. (You don't have to do that.
You can leave in pan for 10 minutes, then put out on rack to cool, especially if you are going to put icing or glaze on.)
You can also make this in three layers.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain well.
Set aside.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place triangles with elongated points toward center in a greased 12-inch deep dish pizza pan.
Press bottom and sides to form a crust and seal perforations in dough.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on lower oven rack.
(Crust will be puffy when removed from the oven.)
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: aloha supreme
directions: Mix according to box directions, except omit water and add 1 can mandarin oranges plus juice.

title: enchilada
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic powder, cumin, salt and pepper.
Drain excess grease.
Return to pan; add black olives and approximately 1 pound of Velveeta.
Heat until cheese is melted. Place 1 tablespoon of meat in tortilla shell and shape like a taco.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour 1 can of enchilada sauce plus 1/2 can of water over enchiladas.
Top with chunks of remaining Velveeta.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, pecans, oleo and 3 tablespoons of sugar; press in an oblong Pyrex dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: chocoroons
directions: Cream together first 7 ingredients.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until light golden brown.

title: broccoli and cheese bake
directions: Steam broccoli as directed on package until tender.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Drain and add broccoli to butter and stir in cheese until melted.
Crumble crackers on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown onion, sausage and pepper in skillet.
Drain off excess grease.
While this is cooking, cook macaroni and drain.
Mix everything together in skillet.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle cheese over casserole and melt in oven.
Makes 1 large or 2 small casseroles.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat thoroughly cup of water and egg, oil, mustard, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Cook jell and vinegar in 1-quart heavy saucepan until smooth; then add 1 1/4 cups boiling water, bring to a boil. Blend in other ingredients, beat hard until smooth after removing from heat.

title: low-fat glorified rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix first three ingredients (margarine, flour and pecans) and press into bottom of pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: quick pepper jelly
directions: Combine jelly and pepper flakes in small pan.
Cook, stirring, over low heat until melted (approximately 5 minutes).
Transfer to small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: zucchini oatmeal bread
directions: About 4 hours before serving or day ahead:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, mix flour, oats, sugar, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Let cheeses stand at room temperature, add lemon juice, garlic powder and red pepper, beat with electric mixer.
Stir in nuts. Sprinkle with chili powder and paprika.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients about 30 minutes until tender.
Add milk and soups; stir until soups dissolve.
Melt Velveeta cheese in soup; heat through.
Serve hot.

title: cheesy chicken spinach
directions: Defrost spinach and squeeze dry.
Spread spinach in greased pan.
Make sauce by blending cream cheese, milk, Parmesan cheese, salt and garlic.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir.
Spread 1/2 of sauce on spinach then spread chicken over this layer.
Top with remaining cheese and cereal on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and top is browned.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles as label directs.
Drain.
Meanwhile, in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook ground beef and onion until meat is well-browned and onion is tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in 2/3 of spaghetti sauce; cook until heated through.
Spoon half of meat mixture into small bowl; set aside. Reduce heat to low and keep remaining meat mixture in skillet simmering.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: In a saucepan melt butter/oleo and cheese.
Sift together the sugar and cocoa.
Then add the cheese mixture and add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and spread evenly into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut in pieces.
Makes about 6 1/2 lb. creamy, inexpensive, delicious fudge.
Oh my!!

title: dump cake
directions: *Can use other pie fillings, etc.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small ungreased square cake pan, stir together all ingredients, except nuts.
When well mixed, stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in pan.

title: frozen bread-caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough, but do not allow to rise.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear one loaf into pieces and drop helter skelter into pan.
Melt margarine.
Add the rest of the ingredients to margarine and beat until smooth.
Pour over the torn-up bread. Tear second loaf and throw on top, trying to fill empty spots. Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: mustard glazed salmon
directions: Place salmon on a piece of foil on a broiler; cut the foil around the salmon and discard the rim.
Put salt and pepper on salmon to your taste.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over the salmon.
Broil fish about 5-inches from heat until done (cut to test), about 9 to 12 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Melt stick of butter in a soup pan; add flour until it makes a thick paste (will have brownish color).
Add the 2 quarts of half and half; stir until thick on Medium-high heat.
Steam broccoli and chop.
Add the broccoli.
Add desired amount of cheese.
Chop the garlic and add the onion salt.
Top the top layer with black pepper.
Hollow out the bread; pour soup into the middle.

title: mock steak
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs and egg together with milk; mix well.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Press in a cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in squares, roll in flour and brown.
Place in casserole and cover with cream of onion soup; add water with soup.
Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour at 350°.
tags: cream of onion soup or mushroom soup

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cut asparagus into 2-inch pieces; mix all ingredients except butter.
Pour into an oiled baking dish.
Melt butter and pour over the top.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven (350°) for at least 30 minutes.

title: never fail caramels
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to 248° or hard ball stage, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Pour into buttered pan.
When firm, cut into squares.
Wrap in Handi-Wrap.

title: coconut layer cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; cream well.
Sift flour and baking powder together; set aside.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add milk and flour alternately to cream mixture.
Add flavoring; bake in 4 layers at 375° until done.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Combine ingredients and heat over hot water until seafood is heated through.
Be careful not to let water in lower pan boil. Serve on hot buttered toast.
Serves 6.

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind vegetables using coarse blade.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to boiling, simmer three minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: blender apple orange bread
directions: Core and slice apples.
Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Place in blender the orange juice, eggs, Crisco and sugar.
Blend well.
Add apples, orange and orange peel.
Blend until fruit is chopped fine.
Add nuts and blend 15 seconds more.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for approximately 75 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk, chopped pecans and lemon juice.
Bake crust for about 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Pour mixture into crust and refrigerate.

title: bread rolls(easy, light and good)
directions: Sprinkle yeast over lukewarm water and set aside.
Put Crisco, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Stir. Add 1 cup boiling water and blend until Crisco is melted. Add eggs, yeast water (stirred) and flour.
Cover and store in refrigerator 1 week.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Put in a plastic jug or jar. Let freeze 4 to 6 hours before serving, shaking every 2 hours.

title: butterscotch drops
directions: Melt together margarine, marshmallows and butterscotch pieces in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Remove from heat and stir in uncooked oatmeal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Press pecan half on top of each cookie.
Refrigerate. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.
No need to bake.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs together well. Add cream of tartar, soda, salt and flour. Press dough onto 2 small pizza pans or a 9 x 13 cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: beef and noodle skillet casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Add chopped onion, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer.
Cook noodles in boiling water (salted if desired) for ten minutes.
Drain.
Add cooked noodles to skillet mixture.
Top with cheese slices.
Simmer until cheese melts. Stir and serve.

title: peanut bread
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and resift 3 times with soda and salt. Blend sugar into peanut butter.
Stir in well beaten egg; beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately, beating, beating, until smooth after each addition.
Turn into buttered loaf pan (4 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch).
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour, or until well browned.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: claire's apricot nectar dessert
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and apricot nectar until thick.
Cool slightly.
Into a 9 x 13-inch pan break angel food cake into bite-sized pieces.
Pour mixture over cake and refrigerate for a few hours.
Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Cut into squares and serve.
Delightful summertime dessert, no baking.
Enjoy!

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Debone. Reserve broth. Cut chicken into small pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix broth and soup and bring to a boil. Pour over chicken. Make a batter by combining melted margarine, salt, pepper, flour, sage and buttermilk. Spoon batter over broth and chicken mixture. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In large pot melt Velveeta cheese in with tomatoes.
Add both soups, chili powder and garlic.
Mix well and heat.
Stir in chicken and Doritos.
Pour into casserole bowl and bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix together oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, corn meal and vanilla.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 250° for about 2 hours or until done.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix juices; add egg and sugar.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Beat cream until thick (not stiff).
Add salt and mix juice mixture and cream.
(May continue beating until well blended.)
I usually double the recipe.
This is good over any fruit or frozen as ice cream.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Beat eggs and mix in the other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Top with:

title: brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1/3 evaporated milk and put 1/2 of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: wisconsin bratwurst(serves 3 to 6)
directions: Also, need paper plates, napkins, grill, charcoal, lighter fluid, matches, tongs, cooking pan and large fork.

title: cochise casserole
directions: Pour into greased souffle dish or baking pan and put in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until firm.
Serves 2.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions tender in a very small amount of boiling salted water.
Drain.
Season with salt and pepper and one tablespoon butter.
Stir in chicken soup, sour cream and pimento until well blended.
Combine half of stuffing mix and squash mixture.
Spoon into a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peach salad
directions: Heat pineapple on low.
Add peach Jell-O and mix well.
Let cool; add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: marie's beefy cheese ball
directions: Mix together and shape into a ball.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: best bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine All-Bran and milk in mixing bowl; let stand about 2 minutes or until most of moisture is absorbed. Add egg and shortening; beat well.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to All-Bran mixture, stirring only until combined.
Fill greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups 3/4 full. Bake in moderately hot oven (400°) for about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: beef brisket
directions: Rub brisket with garlic salt.
Cover with chili sauce and onion soup.
Add sliced onions.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Put in 350° oven for 4 to 5 hours (add water 1/2 way.) Uncover last 1/2 hour.
Add potatoes and carrots during cooking time or serve with mashed potatoes.

title: very strawberry ice cream
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool slightly and set aside.
Beat eggs with electric mixer at medium speed until frothy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Add gelatin mixture, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour mixture into freezer can of 1-gallon electric or hand-turned freezer.
Freeze until firm according to your manufacturer's directions.
Yields about 1 gallon.

title: light date and nut bread
directions: Pour the boiling water over the dates and let stand 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, add the sugar gradually to the egg, while beating with a spoon.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda and stir the walnuts into them.
Add date mixture alternately with the sifted dry ingredients and nuts to the sugar and egg mixture.
Stir in shortening and vanilla and pour into greased loaf pan, about 10 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except some cheese. Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
If hash browns still frozen, bake 1 1/2 hours.
If thawed, bake 45 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: mexican dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread cream cheese into bottom of baking dish (approximately 10 inches round).
Mix together tomato, chili peppers, onion and taco sauce and spread over cream cheese. Spread grated cheese on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and blend.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: quick and easy chicken pie(for the working wife)
directions: Mix chicken and soup together in bowl.
Pour into pie shell. Cover with remaining pie shell as package directs, pricking to allow steam to escape.
Cook as directed on pie crust package.

title: salmon pocket dinner for one
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones if desired.
Reserve juice.
Spread butter on a double piece of foil.
Layer vegetables on foil.
Add seasonings and crumble bouillon cubes over all. Sprinkle with salmon juice and a little wine.
Top with salmon. Fold foil to form a tightly sealed packet.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage and kraut roll
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, eggs, sauce, salt and pepper.
Form into a 10 x 7-inch rectangle on waxed paper.
Mix sauerkraut and onion and spread evenly over meat.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place in baking dish.
Arrange bacon slices over top.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: apple grunt
directions: Pare and core apples.
Slice into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan to form a layer about 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: knox blox finger jello
directions: Mix both gelatins together completely in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add boiling water.
Let set until cold.
Cut and serve.
Makes 100 (1-inch) squares.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.

title: olive dip
directions: Blend together; refrigerate and enjoy.

title: apple muffins
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in milk and oil. Add grated apples.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mom's fabulous fudge(the best peanut butter fudge in the world by esther peck)
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and milk together in saucepan and bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly so it won't burn.
Boil for approximately 6 minutes.
(Use cold water test for hard stage.) Remove from heat.
Quickly add stick of margarine and peanut butter.
(Add nuts too, but these are optional.)
Beat with spoon until fudge starts to set and the margarine and peanut butter are melted in.
Pour into a buttered pan and let it set up.
This is done at room temperature.
Enjoy the best fudge in the whole world. As a matter of fact, this fudge is the only reason I'm married.
My husband keeps telling me he married me for mom's fudge!

title: crispy pickles
directions: Boil above and pour over cucumbers.
Boil liquid and pour back over cucumbers every day for 3 days.
On the 4th day pack cucumbers in jar.
Boil liquid and pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place meat in crock-pot in the morning.
Add the other 2 ingredients.
Plug in crock-pot; cover and let cook all day.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water and immediately add pie filling and pineapple with juice.
Chill.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together ingredients and refrigerate overnight or 1/2 hour before serving.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Peel, seed and cut cucumbers into bite size pieces.
Soak in 8 1/2 quarts water and lime for 24 hours.
Drain and wash, then soak in cold water for 3 hours.
Place in large kettle; simmer for 2 hours in a solution of the alum, 1 cup vinegar and red food color. Drain off liquid.
Make a syrup of 3 cups vinegar, salt, sugar, cinnamon, cinnamon candy and 3 cups water.
Bring to a boil; pour over cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and reheat this syrup every 24 hours for 3 days.
On the fourth day, heat juice, put into jars and seal.
Cold pack 5 minutes.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and jello.
Then add Wesson oil, milk, eggs (one at a time), strawberries, coconut and pecans. Mix together and bake in 3 layers at 350° until done. Cool.

title: creamy spinach bake
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Stir spinach and sour cream together. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top.

title: lemon chicken fettucini
directions: Cut each chicken breast into four strips and season liberally with lemon pepper, salt and pepper.
Melt 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add chicken and brown lightly on both sides.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer to desired doneness, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: very speedy cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Pour filling into crust.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until set.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over top of pie; bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool; chill several hours (5 to 6 usually does it).
Serve with whatever fruit you like.

title: shake choco chex
directions: Pour powdered sugar and Chex into white trash bag.
Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips together.
Put melted mixture into the trash bag with the Chex and powdered sugar and then shake! shake! shake!

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased loaf pans. This recipe makes nice small loaves.
Bake at 350°.
Makes approximately 5 mini loaves.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream 1 cup brown sugar, oleo, 1 egg and flour.
Spread this in a greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Brush on 1 beaten egg.
Sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 325°.

title: party punch(good old cheap punch)
directions: Add the citric acid and sugar to the 2 quarts of boiling water.
Stir until dissolved, then add cold water, pineapple juice and the orange juice concentrate (undiluted).
This makes 2 gallons.
It may be made well in advance of your party and frozen.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Add nuts; mix lightly to coat completely.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill until chocolate is firm.
Makes about
2 dozen.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and butter for 2 minutes after it comes to a full boil.
Take off heat.
Add vanilla and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir the first 6 items together (broccoli, cheese, mayonnaise, celery soup and onions).
Set aside and crumble the Ritz crackers and brown them in the stick of butter.
Place the first 6 items in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish and top with the browned and buttered Ritz crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until done.
This recipe will serve 6 or more.
(If doubling this recipe, use a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, serves 12 or more people.)
This dish is a permanent part of Potluck's Christmas dinner.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Peel 5 lb. potatoes.
Cook.
Mix in cream cheese, sour cream and spices.
This may be refrigerated one or two days before needed.
Reheat in 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Melt cheese in soup without adding water.
Dissolve jello in water; stir vigorously and mix with soup mixture.
Add green pepper, onion and celery and can of shrimp.
Let set up in refrigerator.
Cut in squares and serve.
Makes one 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Split and flatten chicken breasts.
Place in a casserole dish. Combine soup and milk and spread over chicken.
Toss dressing with butter and sprinkle over chicken and soup.
Top with Cheez Whiz and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ida anderson langdon's old-fashioned lemon pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar well adding the eggs one at a time. Grate peel from lemons, then cut and juice.
Add juice and all the rind.
(The grated rind is what makes the crust on top.)
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie crust and bake in a preheated 350° oven at least 30 minutes.
From that point, test with a knife.
Remove from oven just before it gets firm.
It will firm up as it cools. (I used a deep-dish pie crust.)

title: baked chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Mix milk, melted butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients with liquid ingredients.

title: fresh shrimp fresco(microwave)
directions: Rinse shrimp under cold running water to clean.
Place in 12-cup (3-L) casserole.
Add 1/2 cup water and slices of lemon. Cover and microwave for 3 minutes.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Cook rice in 5 cups boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside.
Cook onions in butter in large skillet until limp, but not browned.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: johnny mozetti
directions: Simmer onion; brown meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Place in 3-quart baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: congealed fruit salad
directions: Drain and save juice; juice should make 5 cups.
Add enough water to make 5 cups, if necessary.
Bring liquid to a boil.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Chill. Cut 4 rows by 4 rows.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
To this, add boiling water and stir.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of cool water. Add salt, eggs and flour; beat until smooth.
Leave in bowl until it rises to double.
Set in refrigerator at least 2 hours before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: instant potato soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container. Yields 11 cups.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans; mix with onions and pepper.
Mix vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper and pour over beans.
Let marinate in airtight container overnight.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: In a bowl, combine potatoes, sugar, egg, sour cream and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients, stir in potato mixture.
Heat oil to 375°.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry for one minute per side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Roll in sugar if desired.
Serve immediately.
Yield 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3 in. loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients together with spoon for about 1 minute.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until wooden tooth pick inserted in the middle of bread comes out clean.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute bell pepper,
onion and celery in 1 stick butter, until tender.
Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Mix
well and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheddar chicken casserole
directions: Mix butter, milk, flour and bouillon cubes; let come to a boil.
Remove from heat, then add cut up chicken and celery soup. Arrange
cooked
rice
and	broccoli
in
a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish;
spoon chicken mixture on top of rice and broccoli.
Sprinkle
Cheddar
cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pie filling
directions: Bring sugar, salt
and 6 cups water to boil, then add clear jell and 2 cups
water.
Pour
over
quarts of fruit; process 20 minutes. Add couple
drops yellow food coloring for peaches, 1 teaspoon cinnamon for apples,
peaches
and
berries
and
1 tablespoon
lemon juice for blueberries.
Makes 6 to 7 quart canned filling.

title: potato tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Stir in Lipton soup and mushroom soup.
Put in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over meat. Place potato tots over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg salad
directions: Boil eggs. Add all ingredients and mix well. How many eggs depends on how big of a salad you want. Great for sandwiches.

title: tarragon chicken salad(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, arrange chicken in a single layer.
Pour heavy cream over chicken.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is white all the way through. Remove from oven to cool.
Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
In a small bowl, whisk together sour cream, mayonnaise and tarragon. Pour mixture over chicken to coat evenly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Serve at room temperature.

title: apricot upside down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Have ready a 9 inch square cake pan. Drain apricots well, saving juice for sauce. Stir in margarine, brown sugar and 1/4 c. coconut together in cake pan. Lay apricot halves, some cut side up and others cut side down with a cherry tucked underneath, in the margarine-sugar mixture. Combine shortening, egg and sugar in small mixing bowl. Beat at high speed until fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Combine milk and almond extract. Add sifted dry ingredients to shortening mixture alternately with milk mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Stir until smooth after each addition. Stir in 1/2 c. coconut. Spread over apricots. Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until center springs back when touched lightly. Invert on serving plate and let stand over cake a minute to be sure all the apricot mixture drops out. Serve warm, cut in squares and top with a little apricot sauce. Serves 6 or 9.

title: crunch drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, at medium speed, mix butter, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture until well combined. Stir in oats and coconut until well blended to make a stiff dough. Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cheese cake without crust
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar thoroughly. Add eggs, then milk and vanilla.
Mix, then add flour, always last.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Make sure center is done.

title: stir-fried green beans with sichuan sauce
directions: Cut green beans diagonally into 2-inch lengths.
Mix soy sauce, garlic, sugar, sesame oil and chili paste.
Heat wok until very hot.
Add vegetable oil; tilt wok to coat sides.
Add green beans; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add broth; cover and cook 5 minutes. Add soy sauce mixture.
Stir-fry until green beans are coated and moisture is evaporated.
Stir in sesame seed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: amanda's elephant stew
directions: Secure 1 large elephant.
Kill, clean and cut in small cubes. Takes approximately 2 months.
Put in a very large kettle and simmer over kerosene heat at 465° for 14 weeks.
