Add carrots, potatoes and onions to taste.
Simmer for 3 more hours.
Yield: Feeds 3685 people.

title: creamy cabbage-pineapple
directions: Shred cabbage.
Grate carrot and dice pepper.
Place in a bowl and stir to mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: coca-cola basted ham
directions: Ham should be on of the precooked hams, not one of the speciality hams or canned ham, just the standard bone in ham in the meat counter.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk together until well blended, then add rest of ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: orange cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and make into round balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill well.

title: cheezy mashed potatoes
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes for about 30 minutes, or until almost tender.
Drain; cool slightly.
Peel and shred potatoes with grater.
In large bowl, combine potatoes, cheese and margarine. Stir until margarine is melted.
Stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Transfer to greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until hot.
Before serving, sprinkle with paprika.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal ,flour, salt and soda.
Add buttermilk, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add peppers, onions, corn and meat.

title: louise's rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter and add to cooked rice.
Add mushrooms and pecans.
Just before serving, add whipping cream.

title: strawberry margarita fizzes
directions: Rub rims of 2 chilled stemmed glasses with water and dip in sugar to coat them.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order given and spread mayonnaise over top.
Cover and let set 6 hours in refrigerator.
Before serving, pour one small bottle Italian dressing over salad, then top with:

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix egg yolks with sugar.
Add a little of the milk.
Add flour and cocoa.
Add the rest of the milk and 1 can of water. Add margarine and cook until smooth.
Add vanilla and pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and add sugar to taste.
Top pie with egg whites and bake until brown at 350°.

title: coffee cake
directions: Sift flour with 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Cut in oleo with pastry blender until mixture is crumblike. Remove 1/2 cup for filling; set aside.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each.
Dissolve soda in hot water; add to the buttermilk.
Stir buttermilk into flour mixture; blend until about smooth.
Pour 1/3 batter into greased tube pan.
Spread evenly over bottom.
Mix together nuts, 1 tablespoon sugar, cinnamon and reserved 1/2 cup flour mixture.
Blend well and sprinkle 1/3 over batter in pan.
Repeat twice more with remaining batter and filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Glaze with 1 cup confectioners sugar.
Mix with 4 teaspoons cold water.

title: hot sweet-n-sour franks
directions: Heat jelly and mustard slowly until dissolved.
Cut wieners into 3/4-inch lengths.
Add them to sauce.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Can be used in fondue pot.
Also can be made ahead, put in the refrigerator and served next day.

title: rice cakes
directions: Cook rice.
Combine ingredients.
Heat greased griddle to 400°. Drop by 1/2 cupful onto hot griddle.
Cook until edges are light brown.
Turn and cook 2 more minutes.

title: american rice pilaff(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heat oil in a heavy ovenproof casserole dish.
Add noodles and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon, until noodles are golden brown.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops (to your taste).
Beat the egg and water until frothy.
Dip pork chops in water and egg mixture. Roll in or coat with the cracker crumbs.
Fry at 325° in electric skillet.
Crisco solid gives the best results.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: party punch
directions: Thaw frozen juice concentrates and mix with other ingredients.

title: hot peppers in oil
directions: NOTE: For 3 bushels of peppers, use two (1 1/4 ounce) jars oregano; for 5 1/2 ounce jar garlic powder; 6 gallon Mazola oil and two boxes of salt.

title: spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in water.
To same water, add garlic, sugar, mustard, soy sauce and sweet and sour sauce; stir well.
Put in oven at 350° and bake for 1 1/2 hours or place on top of stove and bring to a boil, then simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 people.

title: cheese burger tater tot casserole
directions: Press ground beef in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with soup.
Spread evenly.
Cover with slices of Velveeta cheese. Spread Tater Tots over this.
Bake at 400° until cheese has bubbled up in between Tater Tots.
By then, the meat should be done, usually about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chrusciki(angel wings)
directions: Add enough flour to egg yolks, brandy and sour cream to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out very thin.
Cut into diamond shaped strips, about 1 1/2-inches wide.
Make a slit in center of each strip and pull one end through slit.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Store in tight container.

title: sicilian salad
directions: Tear romaine into bite-sized pieces.
Peel and section oranges, squeezing juice from pulp into small bowl.
Thinly slice onions.
To the orange juice, add oil, vinegar and seasonings. Stir thoroughly, then toss with romaine, oranges and onions. Serves 8.
This is particularly good with a pasta dish made with tomato sauce.

title: southwestern chicken with salsa
directions: In large nonstick skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat.
Add garlic; cook until golden, about 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and juice, breaking them up with spoon.
Stir in corn, oregano, rosemary, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes. Transfer mixture to serving platter; cover to keep warm.
Wipe out skillet.
Combine flour, cornmeal and remaining salt and pepper. In same skillet, heat remaining oil over medium-high heat.
Dip chicken in milk, then coat in cornmeal mixture.
Add chicken to skillet.
Cook until golden brown and done, 4 to 5 minutes a side. Serve with corn-and-tomato sauce.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving:
315 cals.; 31 g. protein; 10 g. fat; 70 mg. chol.; 26 g. carbs.; 814 mg. sodium.
Work time:
30 minutes; ready to serve in 30 minutes.

title: layer meal
directions: Start layers in baking dish.
In between layers, spread some of the tomato soup.
End the layers with hamburger.
Pour the balance of the soup over the top.
Bake at 350° until vegetables are tender.

title: ragu manicotti
directions: Cook shells as directed on package.
Let cool while browning the onion in a skillet.
Add ground beef and cook until lightly browned; drain.
Add cottage cheese and mix lightly. Fill shells with mixture.
Lay in rows in square baking dish.
Pour Ragu over and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, checking often to make sure cheese doesn't get too brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Takes about 45 minutes or until done.
Make 2 pies.
I add coconut to mine.

title: bachelor's co. casserole
directions: In oil, saute onion and ground pepper until tender; add ground beef and brown well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 additional minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: low calorie night snack
directions: Mix and drink.
Makes 1 serving.
One serving equals 15 calories or a free exchange.

title: green pepper steak
directions: This recipe makes enough mix to prepare five different main dishes, five meals or one meal (4 servings each).

title: chili with turkey
directions: Place onions in large Dutch oven with 1 tablespoon olive oil; cook until tender.
Add turkey, pepper and oregano; cook until done and remove grease.
Add the 2 cans of tomatoes (chopped), the 2 cans of green chilies, garlic and 1/4 cup chili powder.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining chili powder and chili beans and cook for 20 minutes longer.
Serve with cheese, lettuce, sour cream and corn chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce and lemon juice.
When cool and firm, put on topping.

title: rice casserole italiano
directions: Cook zucchini for 3 minutes; drain well.
Saute ground beef, onions, garlic and seasonings until onions are transparent.
Stir in rice and tomato sauce.
Blend cottage cheese and egg.
Arrange half of the zucchini slices in a buttered shallow 2-quart casserole.
Spoon on meat and rice mixture.
Spread cottage cheese over meat mixture.
Top with remaining zucchini; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blue-cheesed mushrooms
directions: Wash the mushrooms and remove the stems.
Chop the stems and cook them and the onions in the margarine until tender but not brown.
Add the cheese, 2 Tbsp. of the crumbs, and salt and pepper to taste.
Fill the mushroom crowns with the mixture and sprinkle with the remaining crumbs.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Serve as an appetizer or with a meat entree.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; drain.
Add barbecue sauce and simmer until meat is done.
Press each biscuit into a greased muffin tin, making sure the dough is to the edge.
Spoon meat mixture into cups and sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until biscuits are done.
I usually bake for about 5 minutes before adding cheese.
Also, leftover roast can be used instead of ground meat.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix until all are blended well (about 5 minutes).
Place in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: tostado salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Combine taco seasoning mix and salt with ground beef.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine lettuce, beans, cheese, chips, avocado and tomatoes, saving a few chips for garnish.
Add ground beef and toss lightly.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Put cranberries and water into a 3-quart saucepan.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium high.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring.
Add dates, raisins, sugar, lemon juice, ginger, cloves, cinnamon stick and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until mixture is thick.
Pour into 3 (8 ounce) jars.
Cover and refrigerate or freeze to keep.
Makes 3 (8 ounce) jars chutney.
Serve with poultry, game or pork.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix altogether.
Beat and bake in greased loaf pan at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamy baked chicken and stuffing
directions: In a long 8 x 12-inch baking dish, place 1/4 cup margarine. Sprinkle over margarine, about 1/4 cup stuffing mix and place chicken breast next.
Top with cheese slices or grated Cheddar. Spoon cream of chicken soup over cheese.
Sprinkle seasoned stuffing mix over soup and sort of pat it down into sauce mixture.

title: meat loaf sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard and ketchup until well blended.
Makes 1 cup sauce.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Split chicken breasts.
Wash off with cold water.
Roll in soup and milk liquid, roll in crumbs.
Place in buttered dish and drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: cream tuna
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour to make a gravy. Add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Add tuna fish and peas. Serve over toast or noodles. Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: oven-fried chicken(microwave)
directions: Dip chicken pieces in milk and then shake in a bag with coating mix.
Place breaded pieces, skin side up, in a 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish with thin end toward center and thicker end toward outside.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave 9 minutes on High.
Rearrange chicken.
Cook 8 to 9 minutes on High or until done.
Remove from oven.
Cover with foil. Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Let all ingredients get room temperature.
Combine sugar and butter; cream until light and fluffy, about 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly after each one.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Pour batter into greased 10-inch tube cake pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, egg yolks and oil.
Add all other ingredients except egg whites, nuts, vanilla and rhubarb.
Beat well, then add egg whites, nuts and vanilla.
Stir in rhubarb.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Can be baked in loaf pan as well.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain string beans; place in dish.
Mix in cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can onion rings (mix all together).
Place remaining French fried onion rings on top of casserole.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: berry kool punch
directions: With a large spoon, break ice cream into chunks and place in bottom of punch bowl.
Layer with strawberries. Pour Kool-Aid over the top.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll into a ball.
Ball can be rolled in additional pecans for garnish if desired.
Chill.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Core, but do not peel apples.
Cut apples into bite size pieces.
Squeeze fresh lemon juice over apple pieces to prevent turning brown.
(You will need 2 tablespoons of lemon juice for the dressing.)
String and chop celery.
Chop pecans.
Drain pineapple but retain juice.
Add celery, pecans, pineapple and raisins to apples.
Refrigerate!

title: superior meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients and place in large shallow baking pan.
Shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large covered bowl.
Heat sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, dry mustard and celery seed to boiling; pour over vegetables.
Cool to room temperature; cover, and refrigerate.
This will keep 2 to 3 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: never fail ice cream
directions: Dissolve Junket tablets in 1/4 cup warm water.
Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, vanilla and half and half.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Add enough milk to fill the freezer container to 1 inch from top. Let stand 10 minutes and freeze.

title: great-grandma's fudge
directions: Bring to a boil the milk, cocoa and sugar.
Let it boil until it forms a soft ball in a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir until it thickens and starts to form a film on top, until it sort of "sets."
Pour into a well buttered pan and place in cool place to harden.

title: just right stew
directions: Fill large pot 2/3 full of water.
Place stew meat and onion in it; boil until done.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook for 2 hours on medium heat.
Season to taste.
The stew will be done when potatoes and carrots are soft.

title: christmas wreath
directions: In a large bowl, melt together marshmallows and butter.
Stir in food coloring to desired shade.
Add corn flakes until mixture is like Rice Krispies treats, stirring to completely coat. Immediately spoon onto platter into a wreath shape.
Use cherries to make holly berries.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as per box directions.
Blend with mixer the cheese, milk and pudding; mix well.
Stir in whipped topping. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding, starting with wafers and bananas.
Makes a very large amount.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Dip each cutlet in beaten egg and then in Italian bread crumbs.
Brown cutlets on both sides in butter flavor Crisco. Remove chicken to baking dish.
Simmer bouillon, wine and water in pan drippings, until bouillon is melted.
Stir in mushrooms and bring to a boil.
Pour on cutlets.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wall icebox cake
directions: Cream light and fluffy the sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Add alternately the milk, chocolate, flour, vanilla and yeast.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Place in refrigerator overnight; in the morning add 1 teaspoon soda dissolved in 3 tablespoons boiling water and fold into cake mixture.
Bake in large loaf or two layer pans, 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve 10.

title: fruit cooler
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pitcher.
Serve over ice cubes. Serves 4 cups.

title: rachel's famous orange chiffon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add oil, egg yolks, orange rinds and orange juice.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
In a separate bowl, whip into stiff peaks egg whites and cream of tartar.
Fold first mixture slowly into egg whites.
Pour into an ungreased angel food pan and cook 60 to 65 minutes.

title: julie's mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; stir in taco seasoning and cook for a few minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Line large casserole dish with chips.
Pour mixture on top of chips and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: gulf coast stir-fry
directions: Heat oil with garlic in skillet or wok over high heat.
Add onion, pepper, mushrooms and snow peas.
Stir-fry until vegetables are tender.
Blend broth, soy sauce and cornstarch together.
Add crawfish and broth mixture.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Serve over hot rice.

title: delmonico cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening well; add sugar, egg yolks and flour combined with soda, alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla, coconut and nuts. Fold in egg whites. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: breaded steak
directions: Sprinkle steaks with garlic salt, black pepper and chopped onion.
Rub the garlic into the steak.
Marinate in refrigerator for few hours.
Coat each steak in cracker meal, then dip in egg. Coat in cracker meal again.
Fry steak on medium heat until well done.
Serve with lime wedges and sliced raw onion rings.

title: fruit and nut cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Cream together; add melted butter. Add 1 tablespoon vanilla; add dry ingredients.
Add soda and water; add nuts and raisins.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake devil's food cake as directed and leave in 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt 30 large marshmallows in large can evaporated milk over medium heat. When melted, remove from heat and add coconut and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spread over cake.

title: pasta in southwestern sauce
directions: Heat sherry and oil to bubbling in heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and shallots or onions and saute for 3 minutes.
Add sun-dried tomatoes, jalapenos and regular tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, plus marshmallows and store in an airtight container.
To serve, use 1/3 cup mix to 3/4 cup hot water.

title: united airlines cream cheese icing
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine with powdered sugar, vanilla and lemon juice until slightly fluffy.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: "meat balls for 50"(this is a spanish version of meat ball receipt)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tomato sauce and tomato juice, and form into balls.
Place in large roasting pan.
Cover with tomato sauce and tomato juice.
Cover and cook at 350° for 2 hours.

title: potato and onion casserole
directions: Season meat and brown in oil.
Alternate layers of potatoes, onions and meat in greased baking dish.
Pour mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef barley soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine barley and enough water to cover. Bring to boil; cook 5 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside.
In a large kettle or soup pot, heat oil over high heat; brown meat.
Add onion and garlic; saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cooked barley, 9 cups water, bouillon cubes, Worcestershire sauce, basil, salt and bay leaf. Cover.
Simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrots, green beans and Tabasco sauce.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes longer.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: cream tacos
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Put the hamburger in a large kettle.
Add beans, brick chili (if not available, add an extra can of chili beans), tomatoes and cheese.
Heat and let simmer for a minute or two.
Add whipped cream.
Let it come to a boil and turn off heat.
Eat on Doritos chips.

title: bite-size hot dog appetizers
directions: Mix mustard and jelly together in a crock-pot.
Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Add to mixture; stir.
Simmer in crock-pot for 1/2 hour.
Place on party platter with toothpicks.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325° for 2 minutes.
Spread pie filling in 8-inch square pan.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Spread over pie filling.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream.

title: baked crab supreme
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, slowly.
Add cream and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Mix and add salt, pepper and sherry.
Remove from heat and add crab meat.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place half of sliced onions on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that is coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer crushed crackers, sausage and remaining onions, soup, milk, salt and cheese.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel and core apples to make 2 1/2 cups cooked applesauce. Put through colander and put in crock-pot.
Mix in the rest of ingredients; do not cover.
Cook in crock-pot for 36 hours on low. Place in pint jars or freeze.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat.
Add sugar 1/3 at a time until stiff.
Add vanilla, pecans and crackers (fine crumbs).
Bake at 325° in ungreased pie pan.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham graham loaf
directions: Grind meats together. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Mix well and roll into loaf.
Put a little water around loaf to steam it.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt caramels with 1/3 cup of evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until smooth. Set aside.
In large bowl, mix remaining milk, cake mix and margarine.
Press 1/2 of cake mixture into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle chocolate chips and 1 cup of nuts over crust.
Top with caramel mixture, spreading to edges of pan.
Top this with teaspoons of remaining nuts.
Bake for 16 to 18 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: caramelized ritz bits
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease a large, shallow pan.
Combine crackers and nuts in a large pan.
Bring butter, sugar and syrup to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda.
Pour over crackers.
Stir well.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
This is important.
Pour on wax paper, break apart and cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: creamy vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, mix soup, milk and vegetables over medium heat; heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons cold water; add to 1 cup boiling water.
Add sugar, salt, pineapple and juice.
Chill until thick.
Fold in one bowl Cool Whip; combine with cake pieces.
Line large mixing bowl with plastic wrap.
Firmly pack with cake mixture and chill overnight.
Turn cake upside down on cake plate.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: confetti mold
directions: Make single jello (red/green/orange) in individual trays one day before (follow directions on package).

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water stir in pineapple and cranberry sauce. Refrigerator for 30 minutes stir in grapes and pecans. Pour into a 2 qt. serving bowl. Refrigerator until firm.

title: curried chicken or turkey
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender; drain.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.

title: supper corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; pour off drippings, returning 3 tablespoons to pan.
Add onion and cook until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 1 or 2 minutes.
Crumble bacon over chowder.
Serves 6.

title: pizza parmesan breadsticks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease large cookie sheet.
Unroll dough; separate into strips.
Cut each strip in half crosswise.
Twist strips; place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Brush strips with margarine; sprinkle with cheese and pizza seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with an electric or hand mixer, removing all lumps until mixture is smooth. Chill and serve with gingersnaps.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, 1/2 lb. butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder, 1 spoonful at a time, alternating with milk, add vanilla; stir in undrained pineapple and juice, blend well.
Pour into a well-greased 10 inch tub pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Turn oven to 325° and bake.

title: divinity
directions: Place in saucepan, over low heat, sugar, corn syrup and water. Stir until sugar is dissolved, then cook, without stirring, to 255° (a little drop into cold water forms a hard ball).
Remove from heat and pour, beating constantly, in a fine stream into the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Continue beating until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in oil; add garlic, tomatoes and 1 cup water. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add pepper, onion and celery; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Stir into mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over rice.

title: crab puffs
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, stirring well.
Set aside. Combine water, butter and salt in a medium saucepan; bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; add flour and stir vigorously until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a smooth ball.
Remove saucepan from heat and allow mixture to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating with a wooden spoon after each addition. Beat until batter is smooth.
Add crab mixture; stir well.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serve puffs warm.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and add peanut butter.
Blend with a fork.
Stir in eggs and milk and mix well. Spoon into a 9 x 5 inch lightly greased loaf pan.
Allow to rise in a warm place for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: apricots and chicken
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden.
Add chicken, garlic, ginger, water, tomatoes, cinnamon, cardamom and salt.
Cover; cook on low heat for 45 minutes.
Add saffron; cook an additional 5 minutes.
Serve garnished with warm apricot halves.
Serves 4.

title: chinese chicken salad(i love this recipe.  . .)
directions: Mix well. Shake just before pouring over salad.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Bake cake and let cool.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix crushed cereal, the oleo and sugar in bowl.
Pat mixture in ungreased, rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Bake 10 minutes; cool.

title: green pea salad
directions: Do not cook peas.
Allow them to thaw, then combine with celery, onion and dressing in a shallow dish.
(For this recipe I prefer Wish-Bone brand dressing, because it has a tart flavor.)

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Mix together the lemon juice, olive oil and Cavender's seasoning.
Set aside.

title: peach fried pies
directions: Cook peaches according to package directions; drain and mash. Combine with sugar, lemon juice
and
spices.
Roll out pastry; cut into 5-inch rounds.
Place
tablespoons
peach filling on half of each.
Moisten edges
with	water.	Fold in half, pressing edges together with fork
to
seal.
In skillet fry pies in 1-inch of hot oil at
until	golden brown on each side, turning only once.	Drain on paper towel.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt margarine; remove from heat.
Add crumbs; mix well.
Press crumb mixture into each lightly greased 9 x 13 x 1-inch pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumb mixture.
Top with chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool before cutting.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cover with 1 c. salt let stand overnight. Rinse with cold water.

title: peanut butter and chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugars and peanut butter in large bowl with mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chips.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar and eggs; stir in zucchini and mix.
Add alternately milk and dry ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is a very moist cake and is great even without being frosted.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine eggs and milk in bowl.
Combine in another bowl the Potato Buds and cheese and garlic powder.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dip chicken in beaten egg mixture and then in potato/cheese mixture.
Put in pan, turn over so both sides are covered with melted margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste and bake in 350°
oven for approximately 40 minutes.

title: creamy mashed potato bake(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine mashed potatoes, sour cream, milk and garlic powder in large bowl; mix well.
Spoon half the mixture into 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 2/3 cup French fried onions and 1/2 cup cheese.
Top with remaining potato mixture.
Bake 30 minutes until hot.
Top with remaining potato mixture.
Bake 30 minutes until hot.
Top with remaining onions and cheese.
Bake 5 minutes until onions are golden.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve dry yeast and 1 tbsp. sugar in a 1/2 cup warm water; set aside.
Beat eggs with electric mixer; set aside. In saucepan, scald the milk; take off stove and add butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix well and cool.
Pour the milk mixture into the beaten eggs and add 2 cups flour and the salt; mix well with electric mixer.
Add the dry yeast mixture to this and beat for 2 minutes.
Add extra flour, enough for soft dough.
Let rise until double in bulk.
After it has risen, put
on a board and knead a few times in the flour.
Roll out into a rectangle; spread softened butter over dough, sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top and roll up like a jellyroll.
Slice and put in a greased pan.
Let it rise until double thickness.

title: taco pie
directions: Prepare hamburger as if to make tacos, sauteing onion with the meat.
Drain excess fat.

title: mexican chicken wings
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Separate chicken wings at joints; discard tips.
Mix baking mix, cornmeal, chili powder, salt and pepper. Dip chicken into buttermilk; coat with cornmeal mixture.
Arrange close together in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan. Drizzle with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes or until light brown and crisp.
Makes 20 chicken wings.

title: danish pastry
directions: Mix about 5 minutes.
Flatten dough out in a square piece. Spread with butter or margarine and fold dough over.
Roll out into square and fold over 3 times.
Let dough rest about 2 minutes before rolling last time.
Cut into desired shapes.
Fill with favorite fruit or almond paste.

title: rich's steak marinade
directions: Marinade overnight and broil on grill.

title: swiss turkey-ham bake
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of butter until tender, not brown. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add undrained mushrooms, cream and sherry.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add turkey, ham and water chestnuts.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with cheese.
Mix crumbs and 3 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle on top. Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 25 minutes or until lightly browned (325° oven if using glass casserole dish and cook longer).

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix persimmon pulp, beaten eggs and milk.
Sift the dry ingredients together and pour the liquid mixture into them.
Stir in melted butter and pour into a shallow greased pan to a depth of about 2 inches.
Bake about 1 hour in a very moderate oven at 300° to 350°.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: jamie's pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet, then transfer to a large baking dish.
Combine rice and mushrooms.
Spoon rice mixture into pork chop pockets.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over pork chops and rice.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then add grated Mozzarella cheese evenly over entire dish. Continue baking for 20 more minutes.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft.
Slowly add sugar.
Add melted chocolate; mix well.
Stir in vanilla, salt and nuts.
Press into well-greased pan.
Chill until firm.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add pineapple, then blueberry pie filling and nuts.
Refrigerate.
Beat Dream Whip according to directions.
Beat cream cheese and combine it with Dream Whip, mixing thoroughly.
Spread over jello.
A few nuts may be sprinkled over top if desired.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage and break up while cooking, then drain.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Cook onion in sausage grease.
Mix all ingredients together except crackers.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: gourmet pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Line a jelly roll pan with foil. Combine sugar and salt in small bowl. Set aside. Whisk egg white and liqueur in large bowl. Add pecans and stir to coat. Sprinkle with sugar and salt and stir well to blend. Spread on pan in single layer. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Stir from outside of pan toward center as the nuts around the edge brown faster. Remove from oven and immediately loosen nuts from foil. Cool on wax paper.

title: easy pot roast and gravy
directions: Flour beef roast on all sides and brown in small amount of oil on high heat.
Remove from skillet and place in roasting pan. Sprinkle dry onion soup over meat.
Mix mushroom soup in small bowl with 1/2 can water.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle chopped bell pepper over meat.
Sprinkle black pepper over mixture.
Bake at 350° until meat is tender.
Gravy makes as meat cooks.
(Do not add salt as dry soup is salty.)

title: corn soup with egg whites
directions: Bring the chicken stock to a boil in a saucepan.
Add corn, salt and pepper.
Bring to a second boil.
Beat egg whites until frothy. Stir cornstarch mixture into boiling stock.
Stir until soup becomes clear.
Turn off heat.
Add egg whites, gently stirring once or twice.
Serve hot.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter or oleo in pan.
Sprinkle nuts, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, crackers and then coconut.
Pour the milk over this.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a large bowl make a stiff batter of the ingredients.
Grease another bowl with corn oil.
Put dough in bowl and turn over to coat.
Cover lightly with paper towel and let stand overnight (not in refrigerator).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with small amount of mayonnaise.
Mix in onion, shrimp, and dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Add catsup. Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: people chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter or margarine. Mix in Crispix until all are covered.
Put powdered sugar into a plastic bag.
Add mix to plastic bag until all are covered.
Spread on cookie sheet to dry.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 pan well. Sprinkle with Lipton onion soup. Layer rice and turkey. Cover with water. Cover the pan with foil and bake at 350° until the rice is done.

title: easy corn dish
directions: Mix all
ingredients well.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs separately.
Add
sugar
to yolks, beat until creamy.
Add whisky to egg yolks
and
sugar,
then add cream, milk and ice cream.
(Cream has
to be whipped until it stands in peaks.) Fold in the beaten
egg
whites
which
have
been beaten and hold in peaks.
Blend all together.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Pour off excess grease.
Add onions and continue to cook.
Remove to a deeper pan.
Add chili mix (add about 8 to 10 tablespoons per pound of hamburger).
Coat meat with flour and stir.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
If too thick, add water.
Cook slowly to blend seasoning.
Optional items may be added.

title: frosted coffee bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add egg and beat.
Add hot coffee, then flour and dry ingredients.
Add chopped nuts and raisins. Spread on greased baking sheet (10 1/2 x 15-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
It should be light brown on the top.
Spread with thin powdered sugar icing and cut in squares as soon as icing sets.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until browned.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Cook pasta until al dente, drain.
Spoon vegetables over pasta.
Contains 6 grams fat per serving.

title: carrot soup
directions: In large pot, pour oil and heat slightly.
Add chopped onion and minced garlic.
Add peeled, cut-up carrots and potatoes. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, marjoram and thyme.
Toss vegetables; cover pot and cook for 30 minutes or until vegetables are slightly soft.
Pour 8 cups of chicken broth over vegetables and cook for 20 minutes.
Puree soup in blender and return to pot; add milk and heat slightly.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on 14-inch round pizza pan.
Top with shrimp.
Sprinkle seafood cocktail sauce next.
Sprinkle onion and pepper on.
Add thinly sliced mushrooms.
Top with cheeses. Serve with tortilla or nacho chips.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: new mexican posole(a christmas traditional soup)
directions: Add posole to water (rinse it first) and boil until it pops. Add meat and cook until tender.
Add spices and enchilada sauce. Simmer.

title: holiday pick-up
directions: Blend
juices in a pitcher.
Chill.
When ready to serve, pour Sprite into pitcher and stir to blend.
Pour over ice in glasses.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute
celery
and onion together.
Set aside.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add celery and onion.
Cook in preheated 325° oven in casserole dish for 30 minutes.

title: mints
directions: *For light green I used 4 drops.

title: spanish rice
directions: Place shortening in pan.
Heat and add beef.
Stir until brown.
Add onion, green pepper, tomato, rice and seasoning. Cover. Bring to a boil. Turn on low and cook 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: taco layered dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given, excluding the avocado dip.
Put this in the center as not everyone likes it and it looks prettier this way.
Serve with tortilla strips or large dip Fritos.
You may want to put an extra layer of cheese.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese and bread crumbs.
Add garlic salt to melted butter.
Dip chicken strips into garlic butter, then into cheese/bread crumb mixture.
Roll up chicken strip and secure with a toothpick.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: amaretto cheese plate
directions: Mix cream cheese and Amaretto liquor.
Spread on plate, sprinkle on almonds.
Serve with grapes, apple and pear wedges.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in taco seasoning, corn, kidney beans, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Serve topped with grated cheese and tortilla chips.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, baking powder, milk and butter.
Add oatmeal and salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan. Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with 1 tablespoon flour.
In a Dutch oven, brown the roast on all sides in half the butter.
Add the water, bouillon, celery, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and cook carrots until medium done.
Layer with onion and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients well in pot.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Pour hot over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream cottage cheese and cream cheese in bowl, adding sugar gradually.
Add eggs and beat mixture with electric beater until smooth.
This takes some time.
Stir in lemon, vanilla, flour and cornstarch.
Add melted butter and mix until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and put into 10-inch spring pan (greased).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Shut off oven and leave in two hours more.
Do not open oven during entire three hours.

title: chicken cheese chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook carrot and onion in oleo until tender, but do not brown.
Blend in flour; add milk and chicken broth. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chicken, wine, celery seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat through.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Garnish with snipped chives if desired.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: delicious pan-fried trout
directions: Heat 1/2-inch cooking oil to 375° in a frying pan.
Remove the head and tail of the trout.
Cut down the backbone, dividing the trout into 2 pieces.
Wash and dry both pieces thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put the trout in the oil skin side down and cook 5 minutes.
Turn the trout over and fry until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Season to taste.
Remove the fish from the oil and drain on toweling.
Serve with tartar sauce or ketchup and horseradish mixture.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, wheat germ, oatmeal, brown sugar, melted butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Press 1/2 into a greased 9-inch pan. Cover with rhubarb.
Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and vanilla until clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in container and freeze.
Remove from freezer a little before serving.
Serve while still icy.

title: warm spinach dip
directions: Saute vegetables with butter on low heat.
Add spinach and cheese.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Spread butter inside of bread.
Warm bread in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Pour mixture into hollowed bread loaf and serve warm.
May be served with cubed bread chunks or crackers.

title: meatless meat balls
directions: Grind with fine grinder or in blender or roll with rolling pin. Mix ground mixture with beaten eggs. Mold into balls. Fry until golden brown. Simmer meatballs gently for at least an hour in spaghetti sauce of your choice. Yields 18 meatballs.

title: cheese-stuffed chicken breasts with sopaipillas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine parsley, 1/4 cup cilantro, cheeses and garlic.
With fingers, make a 1-inch pocket on rounded side of each chicken breast by carefully loosening skin.
Spoon 2 rounded tablepoonfuls filling into each pocket.
Place chicken, skin side up, in roasting pan.
Roast 25 minutes or until tender and golden.
(If desired, broil 2 minutes for crisp skin.)
In a small saucepan, melt apple jelly; add lime juice and remaining cilantro.
Brush over chicken.
If desired, garnish with cilantro.
Serve with Sopaipillas.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hasty beef and bean pie
directions: Combine meat, spices and Worcestershire sauce; spread evenly in slightly greased pie pan.
Combine beans, mustard and sugar; spread on top of beef mixture.
Place in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Easy and fast to make.

title: veal piccata
directions: Pound veal pieces until thin.
Dip both sides in flour.
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in frying pan over medium heat.
Saute a few pieces at a time, turning to lightly brown each side.
Add butter as needed.
Remove meat; keep warm.
When veal is cooked, season with salt and pepper.
Drain excess butter from pan; add wine, shallots and lemon juice.
Reduce to 1/3.
Take off heat and add 1/2 cup chilled butter.
With small whip, lightly blend to a creamy texture.
Pour sauce over veal; serve immediately.

title: nancy's vegetable soup(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients with 1 1/2 cups water in 2 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until piping hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put tomatoes with juice in large pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir well.
Simmer covered for about 2 hours.
You may have to add a little water as the soup cooks.
You can use V-8 tomato juice.

title: arkansas pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.
Chopped nuts may be added.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
(I mix this in a cup with a little more water.)
Add to buttermilk.
Mix liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Place on floured board and knead.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown enough for you.
Put leftover dough in covered bowl or plastic bag and refrigerate.
Will keep 2 weeks.
(I prefer to use dough within a week.)

title: swiss miss mix
directions: Sift all ingredients into a bowl.
Mix and resift.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool slightly. Leave in pan.
Use a fork to make several holes in the cake. Bring sugar, milk and vanilla to a boil.
Add vanilla.
Pour over warm cake.
Cool and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut generously over top.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to package directions. Drain.
Cut cheese into small pieces and mix with broccoli and rice.
Stir in chicken soup (undiluted).
Bake in casserole dish, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butter beans and ham
directions: Half fill a large saucepan with water and stir in the beans, ham hock, the quartered onion, garlic and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour or until the beans are tender.
Drain the beans, reserving all of the liquid and discarding the onions, garlic and bay leaves.
Transfer the beans to a bowl and the ham hock to a cutting board.
Cut the meat into small pieces.
Discard the bone.

title: square meal coconut pecan pie
directions: Thoroughly combine eggs, sugar, margarine, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour in the unbaked pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until the filling is set.

title: rotini santornini bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Lightly grease a 3 qt. rectangular baking dish; set aside.
Cook pasta according to pkg. directions. Drain.
In a very large bowl combine vinegar and pasta; toss to coat.
Stir beans, cheese, olives and tomatoes.
Sprinkle 1/4 c. of the bread crumbs in prepared dish.
Spoon the pasta mixture into the dish.
In a med. bowl stir together yogurt, milk, parmesan and flour until smooth.
Pour evenly over pasta mixture. Sprinkle top with remaining 1/4 c. bread crumbs.
Bake, covered for 25 min.
Uncover and bake 10 - 15 min more until heated through and top is lightly browned.
Let stand 10 mins. before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Scrape, slice and cook carrots
until just tender.
Drain well.
Place carrots in casserole (approximately 9 x 13-inch size).
Layer the onion and bell pepper rings on top.
(Set aside.)
In small pan, heat tomato soup, oil, salt, vinegar and sugar (do not boil).
Pour this mixture over the carrots and refrigerate.
Can be eaten without reheating.
Good for several days.

title: english tea cakes
directions: Beat butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour and almonds, mixing well.
Spoon half the mixture into greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread evenly.
Spread jam over cookie batter.
Roll remaining batter on lightly floured board to just 9 x 9-inch square.
Cut in four quarters and, with spatula, place on top of jam.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove to cooling rack and sift confectioners sugar over top. Cool.
Cut into 36 squares.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Mix with a mixer until ingredients are mixed together.
Put into a salad dish, refrigerate and serve after mixture jells.

title: chocolate fudge ice cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Add vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with chocolate syrup to creamed mixture. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Freeze when cool.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, English peas, onion and bell pepper. Repeat these layers.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour this over the lettuce layers.
Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese on next and then top with bacon bits.
Chill at least 5 hours before serving.

title: company chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.
Can be served with rice.

title: marinated beans
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper, onion, green pepper and celery.
Let marinate overnight.
Drain beans and pour mixture over them, let stand overnight.

title: philadelphia cream cheese spread
directions: Whisking constantly, cook flour, sugar, vinegar and raw egg until thick.
To the cream cheese, add the bunch of green onions, including a little of the dark green stems (chopped) and the pimento.
At the very end, add hard-boiled, chopped eggs.
Makes 2 to 3 sandwiches.
Also good as a cracker spread.

title: pumpkin stew
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Boil beans for 1 hour.
Add vegetables and seasonings and boil for another hour.
Add more water if necessary.
Stir often.
Transfer to hollowed out pumpkin on tray. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with bread or corn muffins.
Great for Halloween Eve dinners.

title: thousand island salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep a month or more.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Prepare
pie
crust
and
line	pan with it.
Fill with sliced peaches.
Cream together sugar and margarine, then add flour, egg and vanilla.
Spread mixture over peaches and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: fried chicken batter
directions: Using only one cup of the flour, mix with rest of ingredients to make a batter.
Dip chicken first in batter and then roll in flour and fry.

title: simmer all day chili
directions: In a large pan, add tomato juice, green pepper, onion, spices, kidney beans, chili spices and drained hamburger meat.
Simmer at least 8 hours.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Combine vegetables in a bowl; toss gently.
Stir remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill before serving.

title: five-flavored pound cake
directions: Cream butter and oil until smooth and then add sugar.
Add eggs to mixture, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flavorings.

title: new orleans chili
directions: In large saucepan, combine tomatoes, tomato sauce, meat, onion, pepper, chili powder, cumin and cayenne.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in beans and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raisin bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine raisins, butter, sugar, salt and hot milk; stir to dissolve sugar.
Cool to lukewarm. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat well.
Add yeast and eggs; mix well.
Add enough of remaining flour to make a moderately soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead until dough is smooth and elastic (10 to 12 minutes).
Place in a lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover; let double (1 1/2 to 2 hours) in warm place.
Punch down; divide dough in half, rounding each in ball.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape in loaves.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Cover; let rise almost double (45 to 60 minutes).
Bake in 375° oven about 25 minutes. Place foil over top last 10 minutes, if necessary.
Remove bread from pans; cool.
Combine 1 cup sifted confectioners sugar and about 1 1/2 tablespoons milk; used to glaze loaves.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In small bowl, mix cream, oil, lemon extract and eggs.
Blend well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened.
Carefully fold in raspberries.
Bake 18 to 23 minutes at 425°.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well. Spread mixture on both sides of bread. Add ham and Swiss cheese. Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Note:
If desired, add 1 small container Cool Whip.

title: $100.00 cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add oil and beat well. Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Gradually add buttermilk alternately with fig preserves, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in Bundt or angel food pan.
While warm, stick holes in cake with toothpick or fork.
Glaze cake, using a pastry brush.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and devein spinach.
Drain thoroughly.
(Paper towels work wonders on drying in a hurry.)
Tear or cut spinach into bite sizes.
Add mushrooms, celery and tomatoes.
Toss. Arrange hard-boiled egg slices on top. Enjoy with your favorite dressing. Serves 4.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add mashed bananas.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Bake in a 12 x 9-inch pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: party punch
directions: In large punch bowl, place sherbet. Add ginger ale and Hawaiian Punch. Add more ginger ale and punch as needed.

title: bulgoki(korean)
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Can let stand in refrigerator if desired.
Heat skillet with 2 tablespoons of oil and quickly stir-fry the meat (or wok).
Be careful not to overcook.
Serve with rice.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy; add eggs, one at a time. Beat after each addition.
Add milk and flour with salt alternately.
Fold in coconut; add vanilla and almond flavoring. Pour into well-greased and floured cake mold.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yield:
18 to 20 servings.
This cake freezes well and stays moist.

title: chicken fettuccini
directions: Coat a Dutch oven kettle with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add next 7 ingredients; saute 4 minutes or until chicken loses its pink color.
Add zucchini; saute until tender.
Remove from heat; add cooked fettuccini and milk and toss gently.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: life savers
directions: Work out dough and put at least 2 hours in icebox.
Roll out thin and cut out.
Take 4 egg whites and beat a little.
While still beating, add 1 pound sugar.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together shortening, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients at once in a large saucepan and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover halfway and stir occasionally.
This will freeze well and can be doubled.

title: bacon twists
directions: Make up recipe for bread and add bacon and sugar.
Brush with mixture of egg yolk and water.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: mushrooms with cream
directions: Wash and stem mushrooms.
Melt butter in pot.
Add mushrooms and spice.
Cover tightly with lid and cook on low heat about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle lightly with flour and add cream.
Stir until mixed in smoothly.
Cook about another 5 minutes.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Stir together salt, sugar, eggs, oil and flour; add yeast and water. Stir until just a sticky dough ball forms, not too long. Cover and let rise 8 hours or overnight. Divide into 3 parts. Roll out each part like a pie crust. Cut like a pie into 8 pieces. Roll up wide end to point. Tuck point under. Place on cookie sheet. Repeat with other 2 parts. Cover and let rise 6 hours (longer if needed). Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pie filling). Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Pour pie filling on top of batter. Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add garlic and onion. Cook until soft. Add meat. Cook and stir until crumbly.
Mix Hunt's tomato paste, water and seasonings. Stir in meat.
Simmer 35 to 40 minutes or until thickened.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook hamburger; drain well.
Mix in soup.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese and Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: buttermilk corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups or grease bottom only of muffin cups with shortening. Stir all ingredients in large bowl until blended.
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups.
Bake 14 to 17 minutes or until golden brown. 12 muffins.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cut up	pepper, celery and mushrooms.
Melt butter in a large pan.
Add
onions and saute until they turn yellow.
Add green pepper,
celery
and broth.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add cornstarch	mixed with water to thicken mixture slightly, then add mushrooms, seasonings, chicken and bean sprouts.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve
over
mound
of
rice
with
chow mein noodles on top.

title: beer batter bread
directions: It is very important that the can of beer be warm.
Mix all ingredients; pour into a greased baking pan.
Allow dough to rise for 1 hour.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun spiced chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in 1 (10 x 16-inch) oven cooking bag and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine rice, green pepper, onion, celery, thyme and salt in bag.
Add tomatoes and water.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Combine corn and remaining ingredients in large Dutch oven.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
To freeze, cool completely.
Spoon mixture into 1 pint freezer containers.
Label and freeze.
Thaw and heat soup.
Makes 7 1/2 pints.

title: pumpkin cookie
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, pumpkin, then eggs.
Beat well.
Mix dry ingredients.
Drop on greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry tomato jelly
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Boil for 20 minutes. Stir constantly.
Add strawberry Jell-O.
Mix well and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour into clean jars and seal tight.
Delightful.

title: carrot and pineapple bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Stir together next 4 ingredients.
Add to first mixture, then add last 3 ingredients.

title: grandma's spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add gradually with milk and vanilla. Beat well.
Add raisins.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken cheese lasagna
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion and garlic in butter until tender. Stir in flour and salt; cook until bubbly.
Gradually stir in broth and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in 2 cups Mozzarella, 1/2 cup Parmesan, basil, oregano and pepper; set aside.

title: chocolate chip and nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar, eggs (one at a time) and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain apricots and pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool.
Add fruit and marshmallows; let set. Combine apricot and pineapple juice with water added to make 2 cups total.
Add sugar, egg, flour and butter; mix well.
Cook until thick.
Cool, then spread over gelatin-fruit mixture. Spread whipped cream or topping on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: blackberry cake caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar and cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk and continue to cook. Stir until mixture comes to a boil. Cool. Add sifted confectioners sugar gradually until right consistency to spread. Should use about 1 3/4 to 2 cups confectioners sugar.

title: squash casserole #3
directions: Chop your squash and set aside.
Break up your cornbread and mix with vegetables and seasonings.
Pour in broth and add only enough water to make moist but not soupy!
Pour mixture into a casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until firm.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and 1 cup sugar together. Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together in a separate bowl, flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
To this, mix in the sour cream. Add this a little at a time to the sugar/egg mixture while beating well.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water together. Set aside.
Mix brown sugar and white sugar, eggs, flour and cinnamon together.
Add together with oatmeal.
Cook in a long cake pan for 30 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: whipped frosting
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.

title: beefsteak roll
directions: Pound steak.
Spread with stuffing to which egg has been added.
Roll and skewer.
Dredge with flour, salt and pepper. Place in baking pan.
Add water and strips of pork.
Cover.
Bake at 375° until meat is tender.
Baste frequently.
Serves 8.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Coat chicken with seasoned flour.
Brown chicken in butter. Add lemon juice and mushrooms; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender.

title: mushroom bjahi(indian)
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion until clear.
Add spices and salt. Add mushrooms.
Cook until done.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place meat in casserole and mix envelope of soup.
Mix together mushroom soup and water and add to the casserole.
Add the dry rice, cover and cook one hour at 375°.
Add 1 cup cheese and 1 cup chopped green onion.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mrs. b's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; boil eggs.
Cool.
Chop potatoes and eggs medium.
Add onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate. Let stand 24 hours before serving.
Serves 20.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in 9 x 13-inch glass dish (greased).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, heat chocolate chips and milk at 50% power until chocolate is melted. Stir in vanilla. Chill for 2 hours or until mixture is easy to handle. Shape into balls. Roll in sprinkles or cocoa or nuts. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pecan cheese cake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl blend cream cheese, sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 egg until smooth.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
In another bowl, blend 3 large eggs, corn syrup, 1 teaspoon vanilla and sugar until smooth. Gently pour mixture over nuts.
Bake on center rack 50 to 60 minutes, until center is just set and pastry is golden brown. Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Mix flour and salt; pound into meat.
Set aside remaining flour.
Brown meat in small amount of shortening.
Place meat in baking dish.
Blend remaining flour with drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serves 4.

title: alice's sandwich filling
directions: Plump raisins in boiling water (just enough to cover).
Drain. Snip into pieces and set aside.
Shred or grind cheese.
Using mixer, blend cheese and dressing until smooth texture.
Add minced celery and chopped raisins.
Adjust dressing to desired consistency.
Refrigerate.
Serve on whole wheat bread to make sandwiches.

title: egg rolls
directions: In large bowl, add cabbage, celery, diced chicken, salt, Accent and egg.
Stir with wooden spoon until mixed good.
Place a large tablespoon on each wrapper at one corner.
Start rolling and fold corners in; have opposite corner moistened with egg and water mixture to seal.
Fry in hot oil, but not too hot, as they cook quickly.
Turn once; place on paper towels to drain.
Have a large platter ready before cooking to put egg rolls on as they brown.
We all love these egg rolls.

title: swiss 'n chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart dish (except walnuts).
Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Bake 40 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water until just tender; drain. Add onion and green pepper.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over carrot mixture.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Heat sugar, water and syrup until it forms a soft ball.
While it is cooking, beat egg white to a peak and add vanilla.
Pour syrup in egg white slowly and keep beating or it will cook the egg white.
Spoon on buttered dish.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, onion, Cheddar cheese, chopped celery and mayonnaise.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Drizzle oleo over top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Separate egg whites.
Mix 1 1/2 c. sugar, flour, milk and egg yolks.
Cook until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat.
In a baking dish, put a layer of filling, then vanilla wafers and then make a layer by slicing bananas.
Then repeat until all the filling is used.
Beat whites until thick.
Add 4 Tbsp. sugar and mix well.
Put on top of the pudding and bake until brown.

title: refrigerator fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Turn heat low. Cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Immediately add chocolate bits, Karo, butter and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate melts and fudge is smooth and creamy. Stir in nuts and mix well.
Pour in buttered pan and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Combine the beef, onions and water in a large saucepan. Simmer the beef brown.
Add the tomatoes and their juice, along with the vinegar, Worcestershire, chili powder, cumin, allspice, salt, cayenne, cinnamon, garlic powder and bay leaves.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours.
The fat will rise to the top; spoon the fat off.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in small amount salted water in covered pan for a few minutes.
Just before it gets well done, drain and whip in blender.
Blend in onion, eggs, sour cream and half the amount of cheese you want to use.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: braised white beans
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Place then in a pot and cover with fresh water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer uncovered until barely tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup of the liquid. Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a skillet over medium high heat. Add leeks, carrot, celery and garlic.
Saute until vegetables are quite soft, about 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine the vegetable mixture, beans and 1/2 cup cooking liquid in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in the tomato paste, parsley, sage and remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake the beans until piping hot and tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.
Can be eaten cold too.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together flour, spices and salt.
Cream sugar and eggs; beat until smooth.
Add prunes and beat well, add baking soda to milk and add to mixture.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add vanilla and pecans, adding cooking oil last.
Pour into greased 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours at 350° until done.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Chop up tomatoes into bite size pieces.
Combine all ingredients and cook on high until boiling. Reduce heat and simmer until you are ready to eat.
The longer it cooks, the better it tastes.
I recommend 4 to 6 hours.

title: german apple pancake
directions: Use a pan that can also be used in the oven.
Stir flour and baking powder together.
Beat in milk.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spray skillet liberally with cooking spray.
Add batter. Cook on top of range over direct heat for one minute.
Layer apples on top of mixture, then sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Transfer skillet to preheated 425° oven.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes, until puffed and golden.
Remove from oven.

title: pear chow chow
directions: Let come to a good boil, then simmer 15 minutes.
Pack in jars.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on a hot griddle or skillet on top of the stove.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: In a small bowl combine oil, sour cream, heavy cream, vinegar, salt and garlic until smooth.
Serve over salad greens.
Yields 1 2/3 cups.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in egg and bread crumbs.
Brown on both sides in margarine on medium heat.
Pour Prego sauce over chicken.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until the cheese melts.

title: lemon pineapple cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Dissolve and cool.
Add pineapple and juice, cheese and pecans; mix well.
Add Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Mix well and chill.
Cut and squares and serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 12.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, condensed milk, cream, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 1-gallon hand-crank or electric ice cream freezer container and freeze.

title: pork marinade(for barbecue)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover pork chops with marinade and refrigerate several hours.
Turn chops over halfway through marinating time.
Barbecue chops over low or indirect heat until done.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Layer eggplant on bottom of baking dish.
Layer fresh tomatoes. Layer onion and bell peppers.
Repeat layering and top with cheese. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and cook 1/2 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix at low speed the oil, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in pumpkin.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking powder.
Fold dry mixture into egg mixture and add water and nuts.
Mix again thoroughly.
Pour into 2 ungreased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream pancakes(basic recipe serves 6 to 8)
directions: Beat buttermilk, eggs and oil together in a large bowl. Mix remaining ingredients together; stir to mix well and add to liquid mixture. Stir just enough to blend. Spray hot griddle with vegetable nonstick spray and drop pancake batter by the tablespoonful onto griddle. Turn once only, when top of pancake is covered with bubbles. Remove to warm plate when brown on the bottom and serve immediately with maple syrup, one of the fruit syrups and/or applesauce.

title: rice pudding(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine milk, Sweet 'N Low, salt and rice in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook, covered, until rice is tender. Add some hot mixture to beaten eggs that have been mixed with vanilla. Return egg mixture to saucepan and cook slowly until mixture thickens.
Pour into shallow pan and sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Brown sausage and onions in skillet.
Drain.
Add diced potato and eggs and scramble all together.
Place generous amount of cooked mixture in a steamed tortilla.
Excellent served with picante sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: palvarone cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool; roll in sugar again.

title: potatoes with hot bacon dressing
directions: Place bacon on rack in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover wtih paper towels.
Microwave at High 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Wash potatoes; pat dry.
Cut each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices, cutting to 1 inch of end of potato.
(The cut potato should resemble a fan.)
Place potatoes in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, arranging the uncut ends toward the outside. Lightly coat potatoes with vegetable cooking spray.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 10 to 12 minutes, turning potatoes once.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat whites of eggs with 2 tablespoons of sugar and set aside. Put egg yolks in pan with 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk.
Put to simmer.
Add cooked rice and cook until thickened. While hot, fold in beaten egg whites.
Can be eaten hot or cold.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat thoroughly.
Put in long pan and bake in 350° oven until done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and salt.
Let boil on medium heat approximately 15 minutes or until you drop a drop of mixture into cold water and it forms a medium-hard ball.
Remove from stove. Add peanut butter, margarine and vanilla (nuts optional).
Stir until mixture starts to thicken.

title: heavenly fruit pie
directions: Combine milk, topping, pineapple, oranges, lemon juice and pecans.
Stir well.
Pour into pie crusts.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: rich pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine syrup, butter and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil gently for 5 minutes, uncovered.
Stir occasionally.
Cool slightly and layer pecans in pie shell.
Mix eggs, vanilla and salt in bowl.
Gradually stir in syrup mixture and pour over pecans in pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: lemon pecan bread
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: bee sting cake
directions: Beat Dream Whip until it starts to peak.
Add instant pudding and rum.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Measure warm water in large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, 2 teaspoons salt, margarine, egg and 3 cups flour.
Beat well until smooth.
Add additional flour to make soft dough.
Cover bowl tightly with aluminum foil. Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
Pour dough out onto lightly floured board.
Divide in half; cut each half into 16 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into pencil shapes about 20 inches long.
Shape into pretzels.
Place on greased sheet.
Blend together egg yolk and 2 tablespoons vegetable shortening.
Brush pretzels with egg mixture.
Sprinkle on salt.

title: fresh brewed sweetened iced tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water for 15 minutes. (I use my coffee maker and put the teabags in the pot.)
Remove tea bags and squeeze.
Stir in sugar.
Add ice and water to make 1 gallon. Refrigerate.
Even better the second day.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon and flake.
Mix all ingredients, except the last 3.
May add 2 drops red food coloring to add more pinkness. Refrigerate overnight.
Form into ball and roll in the parsley flakes, paprika and chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: broken glass cake
directions: Prepare the orange, cherry and lime jello separately, using 1 cup boiling and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour each flavor into a separate 8 ounce pan.
Chill until firm.
Mix pineapple juice and sugar.
Heat until the sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in the hot juice, then add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix crumbs and butter and press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Cut the firm gelatins into 1/2-inch cubes.
Whip the cream until stiff and blend with lemon gelatin.
Fold in the gelatin cubes.
Pour into crumb-lined pan.
Chill at least 5 hours.
Run knife or spatula between sides of dessert and pan.
Before serving, remove sides of pan.
Makes 16 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain any fat.
Add the next 4 ingredients. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add macaroni.
Put in casserole (2 quarts) and sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 8.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix and sift first 5 ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar. Beat in egg and molasses.
Add flour mixture.
Form teaspoons of dough into small balls and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375° until tops are rounded and cracked.

title: simple stir-fry
directions: *Can use La Choy bean sprouts, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots or frozen pea pods.

title: chuck wagon baked beans
directions: In frying pan, brown hamburger and onion. Pour off grease then salt and pepper to taste.
Add pork and beans and stir real good. Add catsup and sprinkle Worcestershire sauce.
Add brown sugar and vinegar and stir all ingredients thoroughly.
(You can add more or less of ingredients according to taste).
Put mixture in baking dish and bake at 350° until thick about 30 minutes.

title: butter bar cookies
directions: Blend together cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Pat down in 9x13-inch pan.
Next mix 2 eggs, 1 lg. pkg. cream cheese and 1 box powdered sugar.
Put on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: artichoke-mushroom soup
directions: Saute shallots, thyme, mushrooms and red pepper until tender. Add bay leaves.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Gradually add broth, then hearts and parsley.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix cornmeal, sugar and flour.
Add to eggs.
Add butter. Cream thoroughly.
