Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple pie with pet ritz pie crust
directions: In large bowl, toss together apples, walnuts, cinnamon candies, 1/4 cup sugar and flour.
Pour into one frozen pie crust.
Sprinkle another 2 tablespoons sugar into second pie crust, frozen.
Crumble frozen pie crust into small pieces (about 1/2-inch).
Sprinkle crumbled crust and sugar over apples.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven on preheated baking sheet.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool. Serves 8.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Leave in pan.
After it cools, punch holes in cake with toothpick; pour Eagle Brand milk over top of cake.
When cake is completely cool, pour pineapple over cake (juice and all).
Top with Cool Whip.
Add coconut, if desired.

title: peach of a pie
directions: Mix until well blended, then spread on 9-inch baked pastry shell.
Chill.
Drain thawed peaches, reserving juice.
Arrange slices on cream cheese mixture.

title: powdered sugar frosting
directions: Beat egg white until foamy.
Add 1/2 cup Crisco and beat until well blended.
Add powdered sugar, a little at a time.
I use milk to make it spreadable.
Will frost one cake.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown meat in oil, add celery, minced parsley, onion and garlic, cook until tender.
Add water and next five ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered about two hours. Mix in spaghetti and simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in zucchini and peas, and simmer about 10 more minutes.
Serve with parmesan cheese.
Meat and soup base can be made ahead and frozen. Serves 10-12.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add the milk.
Knead the dough until it has a rubbery texture.
Roll it out on a lightly floured surface until it is 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in squares.
Fry sopaipillas in deep fat until brown.
They will puff up and cook quickly.
Drain on paper towels.
Dust with powdered sugar or serve plain with honey.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease an oblong baking dish.
Add the cherry pie filling on bottom.
Sprinkle the sugar over that.
Add the crushed pineapple over cherries.
Sprinkle the cake mix over the pineapple.
Cut the margarine over the cake mix.
You can sprinkle with coconut and pecans, if you want to.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tuna ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat egg slightly and set aside 2 tablespoons.
Stir in remaining egg, tuna, onion, cheese, parsley, celery salt and pepper.
Stir baking mix and water to form a soft dough; knead 5 times.
Roll into rectangle, 20 x 5-inches.
Spread with mixture.
Roll up; shape into ring on baking sheet.
Make slits and brush top with reserved egg.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until golden.
Serve with cheese sauce.

title: apple salad delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together with apples.
Garnish with lettuce.

title: scripture cake(look up references in your bible)
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat in until light. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Beat in honey.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and beat only until smooth.
(If butter flavor is used, add to milk.) Stir in nuts and fruits.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in. Pour into loaf pan (9 x 3-inch) lined with wax paper.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool cake in the pan for 5 minutes.
Turn cake out on a rack and gently peel off paper.
Serve plain or frosted.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Add sugar and flour mixture to fruit cocktail and egg.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
When cool, add Cool Whip to top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a buttered casserole dish.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Brown ground beef & onion, drain. Stir in barbecue sauce, brown sugar & beans. Heat until bubbly. Pour into 2 qt. casserole dish. Separate biscuits & cut each biscuit in half crosswise. Place biscuits cut side down around edge of casserole. Sprinkle cheese over biscuits. Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 4-6 people.

title: spicy chicken and pasta
directions: Cook vermicelli in salted boiling water for 9 minutes; drain. While vermicelli is cooking, mix margarine, soup and cheese.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion, Worcestershire sauce and chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste as needed.
Add the hot vermicelli and gently mix to blend well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and baking powder.
Knead in enough sifted flour to make a dough stiff enough to roll out and cut in desired shapes.
Bake in preheated oven for 8 minutes at 350° until done and light brown.

title: cheese-onion bread
directions: Saute onions in shortening until soft, but not brown. Mix egg and milk. Blend in Bisquick. Add sauteed onion and 1/2 cup of the grated cheese. Blend thoroughly. Spread dough in a greased baking dish (6 x 8-inch or 8-inch square). Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese and poppy seed over top. Drizzle melted butter over all. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut in squares to serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Have spareribs cut in serving size pieces.
Brown slowly in 2 (10-inch) skillets.
Put in baking pan.
Pour fat from skillet; melt butter in skillet.
Add onion; cook until brown.
Add the next 9 ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Set oven at 350°. Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
(Makes 4 to 6 servings.)

title: astronaut roll-ups(child-approved)
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Peel and seed oranges.
Puree fruit in blender or food processor.
Lightly butter 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Using a rubber spatula, spread the fruit into the pan.
Bake at 200° for 3 hours, with the door slightly ajar. Remove when dry.
Cut into 12 pieces.
Place pieces on waxed paper and roll them up!

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Mix mayo, milk and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in sausage, cheese, onion, pepper, eggs and pepper.
Turn into shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: basic or vegetable soup
directions: Vegetables can be raw or cooked.
Also add special seasonings. Place milk, flour, butter, salt and pepper in blender.
Add vegetables and seasonings desired.
Blend from 1 to 3 minutes. Pour mixture into saucepan and bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly, until soup tastes done.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chinese coleslaw(single batch)
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the noodles. Chill 3 hours. Crunch up Ramen noodles and add just before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: In skillet, saute 1/2 cup onion in butter.
Combine cream corn, whole kernel corn and rice.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer beans, mixed with taco seasoning.
Mix avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper; layer.
Mix sour cream with mayonnaise; layer.
Layer tomato, onions,
olives and cheese. Refrigerate unless serving immediately.
Remove from refrigerator about 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with corn chips for dipping.

title: kabooboo bread(sioux indian bread, chippewa indians call it banek)
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening and stir in milk.
Pat out on lightly floured board.
Knead lightly and lift into well-greased skillet.
It can be placed in a moderate oven to bake, but the best is to place the pan over a campfire--high enough so it will bake without burning.
Can be eaten with butter, honey or jelly.

title: grandma's sweetheart cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add flour and salt.
Knead and roll into a ball. Cover and chill for 1 hour or overnight.
Roll into little balls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Press thumb into middle of each ball and, using a teaspoon, fill with currant jelly.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 8 minutes.
These cookies freeze well.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: glorified corn-on-the-cob
directions: Boil ears of corn in pot for 30 minutes. Add butter and salt.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel apples with peeler (adult knife) with children, guiding them through the process.
Place apples, after they have been cut in slices, in a pan with just a little water.
Simmer, with cover on, until soft.
Add a little sugar and cinnamon for desired sweetness.
Yum, hot or cold!

title: katie's granola
directions: Mix oats, wheat germ, sesame seed, coconut and peanuts in a large bowl.
In another bowl mix well brown sugar, oil, honey, cinnamon, vanilla and hot water.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Pour liquid over dry ingredients and stir well.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake 30 to 40 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Cool.
Add 1 cup raisins.
Store in a container with a tight lid.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix together pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Place layer of graham crackers in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, covering bottom. Break in sections to fit well.
Layer pudding and crackers ending with crackers on top.
Boil sugar, cocoa, salt and 1/4 cup milk about 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool until glazes slightly.
Beat smooth until thickens a little.
Do not let get very thick as consistency needs to be thin enough to pour over crackers.
Frost cake with this mixture.
Refrigerate overnight, keep unused mixture in refrigerator.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine the cornmeal, flour, baking pwd., salt and sugar. Add the milk, oil and egg.
Mix well and pour into cake pan. Bake at 450° for about 25 minutes.

title: paella valenciana
directions: In paella pan or large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Remove and set aside.
Keep warm.
In same skillet, saute onion and bell peppers.
Add rice, broth and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add peas, seasoned salt, garlic powder with parsley, hot pepper sauce and reserved chicken and shrimp mixture.
Blend well. Heat 10 minutes.
Stir in olives.

title: shrimp in garlic butter
directions: Place butter in small glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 30 to 45 seconds, until melted.
Stir in garlic powder and parsley flakes.
Place shrimp in a 9-inch baking dish.
Pour butter mixture evenly over shrimp.
Cover tightly.
Microwave 5 to 8 minutes, until shrimp are opaque, stirring every 2 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair pudding
directions: Line long dish or 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Mix the instant pudding with the milk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread half of mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Add rest of pudding and Cool Whip mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.

title: orange buttermilk molded salad
directions: In a large saucepan, bring pineapple and juice to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O.
Cool to room temperature. Stir in buttermilk; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 8-cup mold. Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: bacon pepper bread
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, pepper and undissolved yeast.
Mix milk, water and bacon grease to 120° to 130°. Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add egg and 1 cup of flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in bacon and enough flour to make soft dough.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies and set aside to cool.
Poke holes in brownies with fork and pour Amaretto over them.
Let them sit while preparing other ingredients.
Prepare mousse and let chill for 30 minutes.
Wrap Heath bars in wax paper and dish towel and crush with
mallet.
Crumble brownies into bite size pieces.
Layer ingredients in clear glass bowl starting with brownies, mousse, Heath bars and then Cool Whip.
Do this twice.
I also saved a few sprinkles of Heath bar to decorate top.
Keep chilled.

title: stir-fry vegetable medley
directions: Stir-fry broccoli and red pepper in margarine 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and seasonings.
Continue cooking until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and sesame seed to vegetable mixture; mix lightly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Add seasoning to taste and 3/4 to 1 cup of water; simmer.
Mix sour cream with onion dip and spread mixture into dish.
Cool hamburger and put on top of mixture.
Add toppings.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bacon wrap appetizers
directions: Blend together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Cut crust from bread.
Cut slices in half.
Put a dab of cheese on each.
Roll up and wrap in 1/2 slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crescent snacks
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add dry onion soup mix.
Mix and add cheese. Chill this mixture.

title: garden patch creamed corn
directions: Cut kernels from cob, saving all juice.
Place kernels and juice in a large bowl.
With the dull side of the knife, scrape each cob over the bowl to release all the milky juice.
Add all remaining ingredients, except bacon drippings, mixing well.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine cookie
mix,
egg
and water in bowl; mix well. Spread in pizza
pan.
Bake
at
for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in bowl until light. Spread
over cooled crust.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Dip
banana
slices
into
reserved
juice;
drain. Arrange banana slices,
pineapple and remaining ingredients on top of cream cheese layer.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Crumble up Doritos in bottom of pan. Boil chicken and debone.
Cut chicken up or shred into bite size pieces.
Mix soups, onion and bell pepper in a bowl.
Add garlic powder, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Mix well.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat, onion & green pepper in large skillet until vegetables are tender. Drain. Stir in tomato sauce, corn, olives, garlic, sugar, 1 tsp. salt, chili powder & pepper.

Simmer until thick (20-25 minutes). Add cheese. Stir until melted. Turn into greased 9x9x2 baking dish. Stir cornmeal & 1/2 tsp. salt into cold water. Cook, stirring constantly until thick. Add butter and mix well. Spoon over hot meat mixture. Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 40-50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in long pan. Mix flour, sugar and melted butter together. Batter should be crumbly. Spread over peaches. Bake for about 45 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: gourmet shrimp spread
directions: Place all ingredients in small bowl.
Combine all ingredients at medium speed until well mixed.
Remove to serving dish.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with crackers, toast or bread sticks.

title: cow pies
directions: Melt chips and shortening. Add raisins and nuts. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper. They will flatten out like cow pies.

title: mom's yummy frosting
directions: Cook the milk with the flour until thick, stirring constantly. Mixture will be very sticky.
Cool.
Beat the margarine, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add the flour/milk mixture, beating with a Mixmaster.
Frosting will get light and fluffy.

title: crunchy mallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate with peanut butter in double boiler or in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows. Pour into greased 9 inch pan; chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: fudge scotch ring
directions: Line bottom of a 9-inch pie pan with a 12-inch square of aluminum foil.
Place a custard cup in the center of pan.
Place walnut halves around custard cup, forming a 2-inch wide ring; set aside.
Combine chocolate and butterscotch morsels and sweetened condensed milk in the top of a double boiler; place over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir until morsels have melted and mixture begins to thicken.
Remove mixture from heat; stir in chopped walnuts and vanilla.
Chill about 1 hour.
Spoon chocolate-butterscotch mixture in mounds over walnut halves; remove custard cup.
Decorate with candied cherries.
Yield:
One 8-inch ring.

title: robbie's rich chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Bring water to boil.
Add cocoa and oleo.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add eggs, milk, soda and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Pour icing over cake.

title: blue bird cake for the birds
directions: In a medium-size bowl, put flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Set aside.
Boil sugar, raisins, shortening and water for 5 minutes.
Add this liquid mixture to the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nutmeats.
Spoon into well-greased 8 x 8-inch cake pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve in pieces on feeder tray or ground feeder.

title: macaroni and quick sauce
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; set aside.
Cook green peppers and onion (covered with 2 tablespoons water) until tender (don't scorch!).
Add all ingredients, except macaroni, into 2-quart pot and simmer for approximately 15 minutes.

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter.
Add brown and white sugar gradually.
Cream thoroughly.
Sift flour and baking soda and add to cream mixture.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Press with fork at right angles.
Bake at 325° until brown (about 8 to 10 minutes).

title: aunt bill's noodle bake
directions: Mix together.
Use enough cracker crumbs to absorb most of the liquid.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let stand before serving.

title: low-fat shrimp fried rice
directions: *Defrost shrimp by dropping in hot water.
Drain on paper towels.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and top with bacon.
Let stand 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Melt almond bark in shallow pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cut Crisco and salt into flour until smaller than dime size lumps.
Add cold water.
Divide dough into 8 pieces and roll out. Place apple in center of each crust; fill center of apple with sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Put 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon butter on top.
Cover with pie dough.
Place in pan; bake until light brown.
Serve hot with cold milk.

title: bubble solution recipe
directions: Mix in a large bowl and let stand for at least three hours. Store in refrigerator.

title: grilled hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into patties of desired size.
Grill.
May be basted with Burgundy and margarine.

title: lauren's spareribs
directions: Boil spareribs in large pot for 1/2 hour.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Drain spareribs, then place in bowl with ingredients and make sure all ribs are covered with sauce.
They are ready to be put on the barbecue or in your broiler about 10 to 15 minutes.
Keep turning and basting.

title: super pancakes
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together, leave slightly bumpy.
Pour mixture in buttered frying pan; place in oven.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: paul lynde's stew
directions: Drain all vegetables except tomatoes. Mix all together and bake at 250° for 6-7 hours in a covered dish. Do not peek!

title: christmas cookies (fruit)
directions: Blend oleo, sugar and eggs. Then add 2 tablespoons hot water. Sift together all dry ingredients and add to mixture.

title: too-mama's salad
directions: Drain the beans and peas. Drain and chop the pimientos. Slice the onion and separate into rings. Boil the sugar, vinegar, salt and salad dressing until the sugar melts. Blend in the other ingredients, adding the salad oil last. Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: walnut balls
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Cut in butter with dough blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add walnuts and vanilla; blend.
Work dough with hands to form a ball using 1 teaspoon dough.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cookies may be rolled in sugar or confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: pistachio cake
directions: In a
mixing bowl, combine the first five ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Stir in pecans. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool on a wire
rack.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Heat 1 minute. Stir-fry chicken until browned.
Remove chicken from skillet. Remove skillet from heat.
Spray again and stir-fry vegetables until tender-crisp.
Add soup, water, soy and ginger; heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through and serve over rice.

title: pumpkin cake in a jar
directions: You will need 8 pint-size, wide mouth jars, lids and rings and 8 wax paper circles cut to fit inside of jars.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients, using only 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Mix the bouillon water with the soup and pour over first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: buffalo chili
directions: In large heavy saucepan over medium heat, fry together bacon and onion, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 5 minutes. Add buffalo meat and brown over medium heat.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until buffalo is tender and flavors are blended, about 45 minutes.

title: spanish chicken casserole
directions: Tear tortillas about size of a quarter.
Saute in oil until just tender.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into a 1 quart or 2 quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese grated on top is melted.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain fat off of hamburger.
Combine hamburger and spaghetti sauce to a boil and remove from heat. Turn oven to 350°.
Get a 9-inch square metal pan.
Put 1 cup of sauce on bottom, then noodles, sauce, 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese, noodles, sauce, 1/3 of Mozzarella, noodles and rest of the Mozzarella.
Top it with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove foil the last 10 minutes of baking.
Let set for 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in plain nonfat yogurt.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hot and spicy franks
directions: Melt jelly and mustard on high.
Add franks and heat on low for 15 minutes.
Serve with toothpick.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Strip chicken breast fillets and brown in wok in 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Remove chicken.
Add sliced peppers, onion and minced garlic.
Add sherry, stirring well.
Cook until onion is clear (8 minutes).
Add chicken back to wok; stir well and serve over rice.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Beat egg and add to remaining ingredients.
Dip chicken.
Cook on grill.
Turn often.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In large bowl, combine first 9 ingredients.
Wrap next 3 ingredients in cheesecloth and add to marinade.
Add meat and refrigerate covered, 3 days, turning meat twice a day.
Remove meat from marinade; discard spice bag.
Pat meat dry and dust with 2 tablespoons flour.
Heat oil in large Dutch oven.
Brown meat well.
Add marinade.
Cover.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours or until tender. Remove covered and keep warm in 200° oven.
Strain sauce.
Puree vegetables in blender and return to sauce.
Blend remaining 2 tablespoons flour with 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to sauce with brown sugar.
Cook sauce until thick, stirring.
Add gingersnaps and heat through.
Slice meat and serve with sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix apples, lemon juice, vanilla, nuts and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in greased pie plate at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: copper pennies(marinated salad)
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until tender.
Add onion, pepper, and celery to drained carrots.
Set aside.
Mix and bring to a boil the soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Pour hot mixture over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves approximately 10.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.

title: stuffed salmon loaf
directions: Saute chopped green pepper and onions in margarine.
Add tall can salmon with liquid (remove bones) and warm.
Mix in 2 tablespoons ketchup, bread crumbs and diced Velveeta cheese. Split Italian bread and remove center.
Stuff breads with salmon mixture and cover salmon with slices of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven and serve.

title: white face paint
directions: Mix well.
Separate into small balls and add food coloring. Apply lotion or cold cream to face, then apply paint.

title: granola cereal
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread on jelly roll pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring constantly.

title: meat loaf
directions: In loaf pan combine brown sugar and catsup in bottom.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together to make the meat loaf and form it into the loaf pan.
Top loaf with catsup.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Saute crawfish and onions in butter.
Add cream cheese.
After melted, add cream of mushroom soup.
Add spices and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with dip-size Fritos.
This is also delicious served over angel hair pasta.

title: frantic chicken
directions: Place chicken in skillet.
Pour barbecue sauce over pieces of chicken.
Add water.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook, covered, about 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove top and cook until sauce is thick.
Serve.

title: skillet chicken mozzarella
directions: Cut green pepper into bite size pieces.
Slice onion.
Cut zucchini lengthwise into quarters and cut each quarter into 3/4-inch chunks.
Set aside.

title: rice dish
directions: Mix together.
Pour into an ungreased dish.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Add broccoli, if desired.
Add cheese, if desired.

title: kolacky (czechoslovakia)
directions: Pour warm milk over yeast to dissolve. Combine with remaining ingredients. Place in a large greased bowl. Cover bowl with plastic wrap. Let it rise in a warm place for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix molasses, mustard, vinegar and catsup.
Add milk, soup mix, egg, stuffing mix, pepper sauce, m.s.g., oregano, parsley and beef.
Mix well.
Shape in loaf in a baking pan.
Pour sauce over. Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: old fashion gingersnaps
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, using only enough flour to make a good stiff dough that can be handled easily. Roll into very small balls. Place on greased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: rumaki(microwave)
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in soy sauce for 1 hour.
Roll water chestnuts in brown sugar and wrap bacon around, securing with a toothpick.
Microwave on paper towel until bacon is crisp, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Give 1/2 turn during cooking.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake 45 minutes.

title: japanese chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and refrigerate overnight. Dip chicken wings in flour and fry until golden brown.
When ready to serve, dip the wings in the marinade and place in roasting pan or on platter.
Heat in oven or microwave until just warm.
Serve.

title: *rhubarb custard pie
directions: Pour ice water over rhubarb; let stand for 10 minutes, then drain.
Mix sugar, flour, butter and egg yolks together.
Add rhubarb, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Place mixture in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then 40 minutes at 350°.

title: soup bowl stew
directions: In large kettle, combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
In medium bowl, toss chicken with flour until well coated.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken, salt, ground cumin and ground red pepper until chicken loses its pink color.
Add milk.
Over high heat, cook, stirring until mixture boils and thickens slightly. Stir in corn and shredded cheese.
Heat through. Remove skillet from heat. Top center of chicken mixture with kidney beans. Sprinkle lettuce and tomato around edge of skillet.
Serve with warm flour tortillas, if you like.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "green rice" or broccoli rice
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter.
Cook rice and set aside. Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: crunchy munchy granola
directions: UTENSILS:
You will need an oven (you'll need help from an adult), large bowl, small bowl, mixing spoon, baking sheet (oiled) and measuring cups and spoons.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Put all ingredients in skillet (one with T-Fal coating is best) and cook until completely dry, stirring constantly.
Pour out on buttered cookie sheet, salt and put in 325° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove, stir, salt again and put back in oven for another 10 minutes.
Keep in a tightly-covered container.

title: orange roughy parmesan(microwave)
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese, paprika and salt on wax paper.
Coat fillets with mixture.
Arrange fillets on microwavable dish. Cover with paper towel.
Microwave 4 1/2 minutes, rotating once if you do not have a turntable to use.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk, mixing well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat. Stir a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks; immediately return to hot mixture in saucepan.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter or margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into cooled pastry shell.
Spread with meringue.
Bake in 350°
oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: ortega sombrero dip
directions: Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lite green fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: vegetable crescent snacks
directions: Roll crescent rolls out on a 9 x 13-inch baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, dry dressing mix and mayonnaise. Spread over crescent rolls.
Use any kind of raw vegetables for topping.

title: oh my gosh!  this is great banana pudding
directions: Blend milk and pudding mix together with hand mixer or whisk. Add 1 can of Eagle Brand milk and the cream cheese.
Blend some more.
Fold in the Cool Whip and let chill.
Then layer in a bowl with vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding.
Makes a lot.

title: tidbits
directions: Melt margarine and add spices and sauce.
Add dry ingredients. Put in oven at 250°.
Bake 40 minutes or until brown.
Stir often.
(Use shallow pans.)

title: eclair dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Beat pudding with milk.
Let stand a few minutes to thicken.
Beat in cream cheese; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 pudding over graham crackers.
Add 2nd layer of graham crackers; pour second half of pudding over crackers.
Put last layer of graham crackers over pudding.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain and place in 9 x 9-inch dish.
Combine 1 can onion soup and 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over meat and single layer of Tater Tots.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is a quick and easy dish and so tasty.
It needs no seasoning.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top, if desired.

title: pineapple-cherry dump cake
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread pineapple in bottom of pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sift cake mix over pie filling.
Slice butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until top is crusty brown.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Frost cooled cake.

title: pasta and bacon salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling, salted water until just tender following package directions; drain.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Heat oil in saucepan.
Add onion and saute until translucent.
Remove from heat; add vinegar and cayenne pepper.
Mix pasta, endive, chives and warm dressing together in salad bowl.
Sprinkle with crisp bacon and serve at once.
tags: whole wheat or regular pasta twists

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a large Pyrex dish.

title: mama's pot roast
directions: Preheat Dutch oven over medium-high heat for stove roasting. Sprinkle roast with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown pot roast well on all sides.
Add onion and water; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until meat is very tender when pierced with a fork.
Turn pot roast once during cooking time.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix well and store in cool place.

title: california salad(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Layer ingredients in bowl (a deep glass bowl is nice, to show off the ingredients).
Spread mayonnaise on top of all.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with Saran and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Mix slightly before serving.

title: cool friendship cookies
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients well.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar and press down the 1-inch balls to flatten.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for about 8 minutes on ungreased pan.
(Go by touch; they stay pretty light.)

title: mama's chocolate pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium saucepan. Cook over medium heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into serving dish. Let cool before serving.

title: unbelievably good cheese puffs
directions: Melt butter and cheeses over hot water.
Meanwhile, cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
When cheese melts, stir in beaten egg whites. Dip bread cubes into cheese mixture to coat.
Place on wax paper-lined tray.
Freeze.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat until fluffy the first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and water or apple cider to blend.
Add apples and nuts (don't break up too small).
Put into sheet cake pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves a large group.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Make sure your zucchini is peeled then grate.
Walnuts are cut up.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: campers blueberry cake(method:  grill)
directions: You will need 2 pie pans and 6 clothes pins.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, flavorings and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add milk and flour.
Add coconut.
Cook in tube pan 1 hour plus 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Boil chicken. Cut or tear into bite sized pieces. Put 2 cups cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Dot with 1/2 stick oleo. Add chicken and top with water chestnuts. Mix soups and sour cream and pour over chicken. Spread 1 cup cracker crumbs over top. Dot with remaining 1/2 stick oleo and bake in 350° oven until bubbly in center.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift all-purpose flour and salt together.
Blend in shortening.
Mix egg, water, and vinegar.
Mix in flour mixture until dough makes a ball.
Divide into 2 ball.
Flatten a ball and roll out to a circle on floured board to fit pie pan.
Prick sides and bottom of dough.
Bake 425° for 15 minutes. Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: aunt louine's all-bran muffins
directions: Mix all-bran and boiling water and cool.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs and buttermilk to cooled bran mix.
Beat well! Add flour, soda, salt and bran flakes, Bran Buds or rolled oats; mix well.
Store in large container in refrigerator.
Keeps 2 or 3 weeks.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Then cut into small pieces.
Chop boiled eggs into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and serve in avocado halves or on lettuce.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup over low heat until smooth.
Gradually add milk. In a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, arrange layers of potatoes, onions and sauce.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: lentil soup
directions: Clean lentils and remove small stones or other small objects. Place in a large 4 to 6-quart cooking pot.
Add water and sausage and bring to a boil.
Turn down burner and simmer 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper.
Just before the hour is up, start making the thickening.
Add shortening and diced onion into a large frying pan and slowly brown the onion.
After onion is brown, add flour and make a heavy paste.
Add 2 cups of cold water and continue to cook until you have a smooth gravy.
Take a large strainer and strain the thickening into the soup.
You will have the flavor of the onion, but there will not be any pieces in the soup.
Add cold milk and bring to a boil.
Boil approximately 2 minutes and it is ready to serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add carrots, nuts and currants.
Bake in a greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan at 300° for a little over an hour.

title: double fudge cherries
directions: Mix together Basic Batch, cocoa and flour.
Beat egg with vanilla, cherries and juice.
Add to dry mixture; blend well. Knead dough slightly with hands to fully mix.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes. Immediately remove from baking sheet.
Cool before frosting. Yields 2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: dilly cheese ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine margarine or butter, grated cheese, dill weed and garlic powder.
Separate each biscuit dough; cut each in half.
Place in ungreased pan.
Spoon half of cheese on top.
Repeat layers with 20 biscuits and rest of cheese mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Contains 153 calories, 8 g fat and 8 mg cholesterol.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Mash the potatoes.
Add sugar and whip.
Let cool.
Add undrained pineapple in casserole dish.
Put in 1/2 of the potato mixture.
Layer with marshmallows. Add remaining potatoes.
Top with nuts.
Bake in slow oven until marshmallows melt.

title: ambrosia
directions: In a large bowl, mix both cans of pineapple. Sprinkle powdered pudding on top.
Let set for 3 minutes, then combine nuts and coconut and fold into mixture.
Next, blend in whipped topping and marshmallows.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Serves 12.

title: chesapeake bay crab cakes
directions: Remove any shell or cartilage from crab meat.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients, except crumbs. Shape into six cakes and roll in crumbs.
Place cakes in a heavy frying pan containing about 1/8-inch of fat, hot but not smoking. Fry at moderate heat.
When cakes are brown on one side, turn carefully and brown the other side.
Cooking time is approximately 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serves 6.

title: russian soldiers soup
directions: Melt butter in large soup kettle.
Add onions and cabbage and cook 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients, except sour cream. Cook several hours, at least 2, simmering.

title: salad dressing (old world german)
directions: Cook until it thickens.
Take off stove and add 1 cup mayonnaise.
For potato, macaroni and slaw.

title: cocoa cream pie
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch, egg yolks, salt and milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and oleo.
Pour into pie crust (baked).
Cover with egg whites that have been beaten. Brown.

title: chocolate mousse parfait
directions: Combine chocolate morsels, 1/4 cup whipping cream and water in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate melts.
Let cool.
Stir in vanilla and fold in whipped cream.
Layer mousse and vanilla wafer crumbs into 6 (4 ounce) parfait glasses.
Cover.
Freeze at least 1 hour or up to 2 days. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and mix together with other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Blend and press into 2 x 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix with mayonnaise to which sweet pickle juice is added. Place in refrigerator overnight.
This keeps well.
Makes a large salad.
Yields about 10 servings.

title: favorite fruit dip
directions: Stir together until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit. Delicious!!

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with shortening, then add syrup, vanilla, eggs, water and kraut.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Icing is optional.
